PledgeItem.10701_ItemStory:
Admission tickets for the Fun and Wonders art exhibition, featuring patterns designed by Cloudscape Gallery's Maddelena.
Tickets for this exhibition are highly sought-after, requiring at least six months' advance booking to secure a chance to attend.
These two hard-to-come-by tickets are an extra reward for Maddelena's participation in the design.
PledgeItem.10103_ItemStory:
A model of the giant sword from Superheroes of Justice, sold as a set with the sword model. In Michele's hands, the tiny model performs incredible wonders.
“Go forth and face the difficulties. The light of hope shall not diminish!”
PledgeItem.10101_ItemStory:
A shiny model of the giant sword from Superheroes of Justice. Michele's father gave it to her on her birthday. It embodies her pure faith and dreams.
“With your sword in hand, follow your heart and tear through the darkness! This is the way of gamers.”
PledgeItem.10501_Name: The Spiral of Speech Hardcover Edition
PledgeItem.10701_Desc: Admission tickets to an artistic feast of surprises and inspiration...
PledgeItem.14601_ItemStory:
A tablet with the left side of the screen damaged, once used to record collapse syndrome patient data. It now serves as a memento of your first collaboration with Celestia.
Astral Sanctuary's logo is at the center of the screen, with scattered stars representing visiting patients.
PledgeItem.10504_ItemStory:
A pair of medals of honor engraved with black and white unicorns, bearing the trust of an ancient family. It is said that the recipient will receive blessings from the unicorns.
In the face of time, everything decays, only the noble soul remaining indestructible.
PledgeItem.12801_ItemStory:
A metal pass card with the symbol of The Scissors, gifted by Lawine, marking the beginning of your acquaintance with her.
The pass represents the trust and recognition of The Scissors, granting free access to certain areas of its territory.
PledgeItem.10101_Desc: Every time she talks about games, her eyes twinkle like little stars.
PledgeItem.14603_ItemStory:
A handmade bracelet with the sun at its center, connecting stars and moons at both ends.
The bracelet is made from crystals mined on Old Earth. Celestia's name is engraved on the inside of one of the crystals.
PledgeItem.10501_Desc: Making friends is similar to negotiating - both are a struggle to earn someone's respect.
PledgeItem.10704_Desc: Protecting the most beautiful story of harvest with the paintbrush!
PledgeItem.12401_ItemStory:
A carefully crafted acrylic figurine featuring a Chibi version of Kokona giving a thumbs up.
Bestowed only upon businesses recognized for their taste, quality, and innovation, this badge of honor is widely acknowledged by the citizens.
PledgeItem.14602_ItemStory:
A finely crafted telescope with a metal star pendant hanging from a thin chain.
The tube of the telescope is made of copper while the other components are made from precious wood, retaining the design style of Old Earth.
PledgeItem.12404_ItemStory:
A portable projector capable of storing large volumes of engineering data, suitable for viewing blueprints on the job.
Recommended by senior engineers, it is light and compact, leaving precious space for other items on the workbench. The content stored within carries people's thoughts and memories.
PledgeItem.12801_Desc: Decisive and swift, a captain should lead by example.
PledgeItem.10702_ItemStory:
The creator designed this basket with the hopeful wish of a rewarding journey, decorated with her favorite sweet tea strawberries.
The basket is often empty, but perhaps thanks to the art consultant's blessing, the designer's wish has been fulfilled.
PledgeItem.12803_ItemStory:
A beret and a pair of sunglasses purchased during a sale, with a simple look and excellent UV protection. Given to Lawine after she cleverly handled a crisis. As a result of her careful maintenance, the hat now carries a faint scent and looks as glossy as new.
Lawine cherishes them deeply, believing that they bring her good luck and courage as she wears them out on sunny days.
PledgeItem.10503_Desc: In the arena of negotiation, the dark side faces against the light side as logic and emotions clash.
PledgeItem.10502_ItemStory:
Audrey has collected and organized chocolate recipes that cover over a dozen styles. From ingredients to production methods, everything is included.
Thanks to her dedication, the century-old family stands proud, turning even the bitterest chocolate sweet and crisp.
PledgeItem.12804_Desc: Closing her eyes, she feels as calm as you.
PledgeItem.12803_Desc: Improvise, adapt, and overcome like a pine standing firm against the wind.
PledgeItem.12402_ItemStory:
The Sea Bunny healing drone Kokona uses, designed with her personal aesthetics in mind.
The drone's ears flop lifelessly due to the loss of power. Perhaps it is just tired and only needs a little rest before returning to Kokona. Protect it for Kokona until it wakes up.
PledgeItem.12403_Desc: Kokona's treasured possession, filled with memories.
PledgeItem.10103_Desc: I am Investigator Michele, but I'm also the super gamer Michele!
PledgeItem.12802_ItemStory:
Lawine's personal first aid kit. Simple and modest in size, it is stocked with common medical supplies, especially for treating wounds.
Lawine uses these medicines sparingly, seemingly not caring about her own wounds.
PledgeItem.12804_ItemStory:
Lawine's wooden training dagger for practicing martial arts. It is light, compact, and easy to conceal. The blade is severely worn, marking every training session of Lawine's.
Found on the weapon rack of the dojo, it now accompanies Lawine as she seeks inner peace, whether in the bamboo forest behind the dojo or the moonlit tea house.
PledgeItem.14604_Desc: An electric sparkler that emits a gentle glow.
PledgeItem.14602_Desc: Celestia's childhood favorite, now with new meaning.
PledgeItem.12401_Desc: Acknowledgement from the gourmet street food.
PledgeItem.10102_ItemStory:
The Painting Utopia Security badge embodies the spirit of perseverance of past investigators, with the sword of justice piercing through it, its valiant glory still shining.
“Justice, bravery, and perseverance - this is the motto of P.U.S.”
“By wearing this badge, I, too, can become a hero!”
PledgeItem.14603_Desc: A bracelet of Celestial bodies, engraved with Celestia's name.
PledgeItem.10704_ItemStory:
One of Maddelena Leary's signature pieces, created with the help of her consultant using paint made from berries, featuring every specialty product of Berrytown.
However, there are few who can pronounce the full name of this heartwarming artwork.
PledgeItem.10703_ItemStory:
Madelena's favorite paintbrushes and the Kaleidoscope palette, covered in paint made from berries.
Maddelena received Kaleidoscope on her 7th birthday. Despite it being stained over time, Maddelena still uses it to mix colors every time she paints.
PledgeItem.10704_Name: Sweet and Dreamy: Story of Harvest IV
PledgeItem.10501_ItemStory:
Written by Audrey's parents, the negotiation handbook contains comprehensive techniques and expertise, helping Audrey emerge victorious in countless negotiations.
The first page reads, “To Audrey Grove, our most beloved daughter.”
PledgeItem.10504_Desc: The pride and purity of the storied family flow within it.
PledgeItem.14601_Desc: A memento of your first collaboration.
PledgeItem.10503_ItemStory:
A simple, classic bone china coffee cup, a birthday gift given by her parents. Audrey seldom uses it due to her dislike of coffee.
The coffee carries the flavor of memories, witnessing the gatherings and partings of an ancient family.
PledgeItem.10104_ItemStory:
When Michele received a gift of appreciation for her gamer's style for the first time, she engraved her beliefs on the trophy, protecting the cat paw cookies inside.
“To the amazing cat detective, your courage and perseverance are not different from those of the hero in the game.”
PledgeItem.10502_Desc: Through the creator's ingenuity, the chocolate was sculpted from its molten state.
PledgeItem.10703_Desc: The palette and colors are not unlike the artist and the consultant.
PledgeItem.12802_Desc: As a weapon of destruction of The Scissors, Lawine sweeps through enemy lines like a raging flame.
PledgeItem.10702_Desc: The fruit basket is filled with inspiration!
PledgeItem.10102_Desc: I alone have to uphold what the badge represents.
PledgeItem.14604_ItemStory:
An electronic device that simulates fireworks by emitting beams of light. Its safe and harmless design completely replaces traditional gunpowder fireworks.
While its electronic design fits the style of Strinova, it is actually an item from Old Earth.
PledgeItem.12403_ItemStory:
A replica of an oddly shaped ancient doll, a cultural heritage of Old Earth.
Even among the many unique gifts Kokona has received, this stands out as particularly unusual. Rumor has it that Kokona once used it to play house.
PledgeItem.10104_Desc: What lies beyond the door? The girl gathers her courage and opens the door...

ReturnLetterCfg.10005_LetterTitleTwo:
The next taste-testing event is about to begin!
The competition has gotten way more fierce. Everyone seems super motivated to earn “Kokona's approval”.
I wonder what kind of food will be on offer this time? Who's gonna win the grand prize?
It's so hard to decide! Even thinking about it makes my head spin!
Navigator, will you join me?

Hehe... When I'm with you, it feels like I never run out of things to say.
I look forward to sitting with you at the food stall after work, chatting about this and that while we enjoy tasty skewers and sweet soda.
I hope that day will come soon - don't keep me waiting!
ReturnLetterCfg.10004_LetterTitleTwo:
Perhaps that's beyond my reach.
But that doesn't mean I'm going to give up. I'll keep chasing your shadow, no matter how long it takes.

On another note, I've planted some new flowers at home.
After some time, maybe around when you return -
They'll be able to bloom.
When the time comes, please come visit.
I wonder how it will feel - to drink tea and look at the flowers with you once more.

When I think about it, there are so many things I want to do with you.
Our bond still has a long way to go.
In the future, I'm sure the threads of our lives will wind an even more beautiful tapestry.
ReturnLetterCfg.10001_LetterTitle:
Do you remember those days when we gazed at the stars together...?
I showed you how, when the stars thin out at the horizon and four bright ones emerge, it signals the onset of autumn. 
I wonder when the next autumn will come...

While you've been away, I've continued to observe many distant celestial bodies alone.
They're both captivating and mysterious.
Among them, there's a splendid star cluster about 5,200 light-years from Earth, adorned with colors as deep and vivid as flowers.
In the old astronomical records of Earth, it is called the 'Rosette Nebula', where each petal cradles the birth of new stars.
ReturnLetterCfg.10005_LetterTitle:
Heya partner. It's been a while!
What kind of adventures have you been on?
You must have come across so many new and wonderful things to have been away for so long.

It's a shame that I can't join you out there.
I've many important friends here to protect. Many juniors to set an example for.
But it's not boring, either. Our world is also changing rapidly, with many new things happening every day.
While you've been away, everyone's been working hard to protect this world and make it a better place. If you return, you should take a look around at all the changes that have occurred

Oh! One more thing -
ReturnLetterCfg.10001_LetterTitleTwo:
In our world, the first observer can claim nominal ownership of a star.
This bouquet of stars, had it not been discovered by an observer from Strinova, would have faded into the oblivion of time.
Fortunately, I was the first to discover it—how magnificent this cluster of roses in the nebula is...

When the stars next align, would you be so kind as to join me in gazing upon it?
How wonderful it would be if I could sit with you under the autumn night, counting the stars one by one...
ReturnLetterCfg.10002_LetterTitle:
Long time no see, partner!
Do you still remember that wish we made together?
You would be the “Mighty Meow”, and I would be the “Mini Meow.”
Let's walk hand in hand and become the heroes of the next generation of Superheroes of Justice!

Partner, have you heard of all that's happened while you were away?
Some players have adapted our experiences into fanfiction and posted them all over the Internet!
These stories have sparked a big response from the community.
Even game studios found the story of the Cat Inspector and Navigator to be super interesting.
This part is gonna shock you! They decided to -
ReturnLetterCfg.10006_LetterTitle:
Navigator! I'm starting to think you've forgotten about me!
What have you been up to lately? Still doing overtime at the Astral Sanctuary?
To be honest, I'm about the same... The Cloudscape Gallery recently got commissioned to create a huge exhibition.
Word on the street is that it's being funded by our boss and the Grove family. The scale is meant to be as big as the “Headturner” exhibition.

Fortunately enough, I was able to put all the materials we collected in Berrytown to use, and my design was selected!
Maybe I even have the chance to win a Best Creation award!
I hope you'll be able to see it too...

One more thing...
ReturnLetterCfg.10004_LetterTitle:
Navigator, how long has it been since we've last seen one another?

I'm still a loyal patron of my favorite teahouse.
Feeling the cool breeze bow through the bamboo, I can't help but be reminded of...
Those days we sparred and sampled tea together.
For some reason, I always felt like something was missing - something that would give the tea in my cup the flavor I was used to.
Sure enough, it does feel rather lonely without you around.

Don't worry! I've been keeping up my practice, even while you're gone.
The more I practice, the more amazed I become at your tactics.
I wonder how long it will take me to achieve your focus in battle.
ReturnLetterCfg.10006_LetterTitleTwo:
I tried out a few new dishes on my family - stuff like chicken-fried steak, macaroni, and lasagna...
The feedback I've received is that they're as delicious as they are artistic!
When you have time, I'd love to invite you over.
Let's enjoy a long-overdue dinner.

To make a unique and delicious dish, you've got to use seasonings that people wouldn't expect!
I'm hoping you'll come back soon. I'm not the same artist without your inspiration and support.
Navigator, I've found a lot of good places to collect materials for my art. I'd love to visit them with you.
ReturnLetterCfg.10003_LetterTitleTwo:
But I wonder, can I really convey that sincerity that you spoke about?
My heart was uneasy, though full of hope.
Hmpf... With my skills, isn't success a forgone conclusion?

Of course... I wouldn't have been able to create such precious memories alone.

So, if just to commemorate that memory, why don't you join me for a tea party?
The pure unicorn represents my sincere feelings.
The warmth of the black tea represents my passionate heart.
At this moment, I formally extend an invitation to you, my comrade.

The venue will be somewhere most appropriate - my home.
Black tea, chocolate, and so long as you'll humor me...
I would be happy to play a song for you once more.
ReturnLetterCfg.10002_LetterTitleTwo:
Make the two of us the heroes of the next generation!

The devs have already sent me a copy of the demo.
I've no idea what the story is like, but I'm looking forward to finding out!
The dream I've held for many years has finally come true, and it's even with my trusted partner!
I had many nights of sweet dreams...

That's why... Partner, you've gotta come back, and quick!
I've already got the consoles all ready to go!
This time, there won't be any “Mighty Meow” or “Mini Meow.”
We'll play our own roles as we write a heroic story with our own hands!
ReturnLetterCfg.10003_LetterTitle:
It's been a while since we've seen each other.
Are you also busy with work?
Ah! Don't take things the wrong way. I'm writing this letter... Just as a routine gesture between comrades.

I've been very busy with the R&D of new products for the Hermes store.
Let me give you a preview!
We've got our eyes on the sweets market, and we're getting ready to launch a chocolate...
You remember, right? It was that one we came up with together.
The notes I've decided for this chocolate are “memory” and “sincerity.”

RoleBiography.14605_StoryContent:
- “Celestia, why don't Mom and Dad remember me anymore?”
The question was asked by a young patient sent to the Astral Sanctuary. Celestia mulled over how to respond.
Children cannot understand the complexities of collapse syndrome, but they can see its effects on people. Someone they know will suddenly change in temperament, become argumentative, and start having endless quarrels, frictions, and conflicts with their relatives - a once-happy family completely destroyed.
In the face of the child's personal pain, it felt as if any words she could speak would be powerless to heal his wounds.
Celestia didn't have a response. She knew that his parents were still alive, but with the affliction of collapse syndrome, they might as well have been different people. What would happen to the children left behind? What would be their future?
She would do her best to calm the mind of the young ones under her care. As she gazed upon their young sleeping faces, she imagined that she could heal the scars deep within their minds, bit by bit.
Urbino's funding solved her financial issues, but Celestia still lacked reliable partners. Her only choice was to take on more and more work. Early days and long nights became commonplace. To keep herself awake, Celestia came up with a brew she called Starlight Coffee. The bittersweet and refreshing drink became one of her daily little pleasures.
The Astral Sanctuary has gradually earned a reputation. Those who have received her care will never forget Celestia. But she remained alone.
At least, until the Navigator came into her life...
Perhaps Celestia, regarded as a “star” by her patients, will finally receive a “star” of her own?
RoleBiography.12404_StoryContent:
“Your first piece of homework will be finding him a soul.”
Her teacher's words sent Kokona into a deep period of contemplation.
Kokona's interest in robotics stemmed entirely from her unceasing curiosity about the new. But she had never given much thought to the purpose of her designs. Kokona resolved to find a task befitting of Mister Sea Bunny.
His light frame provided excellent aerodynamics. He had a wide field of vision. His small size meant he could squeeze through gaps and navigate difficult terrain. The most suitable task would be...
“Arrrrgh! I've got nothing!!” Kokona scratched her head in distress as she paced through camP.U.S.
Attention drawn by the ruckus, a girl slightly younger than Kokona popped her head around the corner. “Excuse me - is there something bothering you?”
Perhaps she just needed someone to vent to. Kokona wasn't expecting much. Nevertheless, she painstakingly repeated the story of her assignment and Mister Sea Bunny's past and present life.
“If that's the case, why don't you just ask him? If he could choose, what would Mister Sea Bunny like to do?”
Before she could say anything else, the girl was quickly called away by an older woman bearing the uniform of a P.U.S executive.
Kokona can still clearly recall the brilliant starry pattern on that girl's dress, along with her carefree advice.
RoleBiography.10503_StoryContent:
“People's hearts are unpredictable, but our family ties are indestructible.”
Audrey once held the same belief as her father - that those who shared their name would uphold the nobility and dignity of their house as they strove so hard to.
Though there were rumors that Blaise Grove had long coveted the role of family patriarch, Audrey was not one to suspect her own flesh and blood... But all this meant was that what happened was even more of a surprise.
The company's executive director was assassinated, her parents' safety was threatened, and the company entered a deep crisis.
In a calculated strike, Blaise's faction in the family defected en masse, selling their stocks to competitors at discount prices, resulting in huge losses to the family's position.
When Audrey and her father attempted to take charge of the situation and rally the family, their speeches were met with ridicule and blank stares. Having seized control of the narrative, their opponents called for a vote and ruthlessly expelled father and daughter from the family.
The sudden betrayal made Audrey raise her defenses even higher. She could trust no one but her parents.
To preserve what remained of the family's business, Audrey announced that she would be delisting the company as she explored new avenues.
Now a house divided, the outside world sees the sun setting on the Grove family. But Audrey knows that a true Grove stands proud and unyielding, pure and eternal.
RoleBiography.12403_StoryContent:
“I only found out later that Mister Sea Bunny looks nothing like his namesake at all! His body isn't soft and gooey at all! He even short-circuits when I put him in water...”
“Please wait a moment, Kokona.” The admissions officer tried collecting themselves from the girl's long-winded rant.
“We already know that you have great affection for this... housekeeping bot. We do appreciate your interest in robotics, but I feel obliged to say that we won't be able to admit you based on just that.”
“Don't worry! Don't worry! There's more to my story. After that, I dismantled Mister Sea Bunny down to his core components!”
“You're saying you managed to disassemble a robot at such a young age? Impressive, but I'll need to hear more.”
“What if I told you I put him back together? Check it out! Doesn't he look more like a sea bunny now?”
“Hm. Not bad for a student. But there's a fatal flaw.”
Faced with Kokona's blank expression, the admissions officer let out a sigh.
“Listen carefully. What you have now is just an empty shell with a cute face. Kokona, machines should also have their own souls.”
Kokona let out a slight frown of dejection. She had never thought about this.
The admissions officer was right. She had turned Mister Sea Bunny into nothing more than a sophisticated toy.
She wasn't looking forward to telling her parents about this rejection...
...
“Your first piece of homework will be finding him a soul.”
“Eh? So you're saying...”
“That's right. You've been admitted. Welcome to the Wright Institute of Technology. One more thing - It's 'teacher' from now on.”
RoleBiography.12402_StoryContent:
“Happy birthday, Kokona! This gift is a little different than usual. It'll be able to tell you stories while we're away. Love, mom and dad.”
Kokona always received a letter and gift from her far-away parents for her birthday. The contents would vary greatly from year to year, from strange dolls to exquisite fabrics... Every time Kokona was about to open a gift, she would make a guess and comment on what she received during the next video call. It was the special little ritual of her family.
Kokona would have never been able to guess what she received this time - a round, barrel-shaped housekeeping bot.
Though she'd seen all manner of strange antiques and artifacts, this was the first time Kokona had come into contact with such advanced technology.
Boasting a simple design, powerful, cutting-edge materials, and the power of AI, these bots gave Kokona an entirely new sense of wonder.
When she pressed the power button, the sensor on the top of the bot would spin around like a pair of rabbit ears.
“Mister Robot, are you a rabbit? What's up with the pair of long ears?”
“Correction. The 'antennas' on this device are biosensors designed to imitate those on sea bunnies.”
“So... You're not a rabbit? Should I call you Mister Sea Bunny?”
“Unknown command. Owner may be attempting to register 'Mister Sea Bunny' as the username of this machine. Please confirm.”
“I don't get it... Mister Sea Bunny, won't you please tell me your story?”
RoleBiography.10501_StoryContent:
“I shall stand proud and unyielding, pure and eternal.”
Such was the oath young Audrey swore to the Grove family's ancestral crest - a unicorn in pure white.
As a member of the Grove family, the daughter of its patriarch no less, Audrey was taught from a young age to always carry herself with elegance and nobility and never give in easily.
Planned to the letter by her strict parents, Audrey's childhood was filled with over ten lessons a day, covering everything from equestrianism and negotiation to finance, music, and dance...
Audrey has always been exceptional - a rarefied talent capable of mastering new things far faster than her peers.
Though the honor and responsibility of the Grove family name may have been a burden to many, Audrey saw things differently.
When she was alone and gazing upon the metal in her hand, she sincerely hoped that one day she could shine with the same noble brilliance.
Perhaps out of willfulness or perhaps out of a daughter's sincere wish, Audrey occasionally invited her parents to musical tea parties - this was the only request she ever made of them.
Only with coffee, chocolate, the soothing sounds of the violin, and the entire family being together would such a tea party be complete.
As bow and string danced together in a wonderful symphony and an angelic sound filled the room, the girl seemed enveloped in a pure white glow.
RoleBiography.10101_StoryContent:
“Promise me, partner, that you will return in one piece!”
“You got it. A gamer always keeps their promise!”
Every time Investigator George Lee goes on a field mission, he says goodbye to his dear daughter like this.
Promises between two gamers must be fulfilled.
Every time George leaves for work, he returns on time to play with Michele her favorite game - Superheroes of Justice. Playing games sat in front of the television is one of the few moments the father can spend with her daughter.
George controls Mighty Meow, the protagonist, while Michele takes his partner, Pawtector. Together, the duo takes on the evil dragon.
It takes courage and innovation to beat a game as fast as possible. This method helps Michele gradually form her unique gamer mindset and become a skilled player.
She unconsciously applies this mindset to real life, adopting a bold and unconventional approach to things.
The open-minded George fully supports Michele, encouraging her to try anything she wants to do.
“Follow your heart and try bravely without second-guessing yourself. That's what gamers do.”
RoleBiography.10104_StoryContent:
“It'll probably be a long time before I can return.”
“Just how long is that...? Don't worry. No matter how long it takes, I'll be waiting for you.”
Those words were Michele's last farewell to her father. It was raining heavily. Michele's father took urgent steps with a grave look on his face.
It was the first time that he hadn't promised a day in which he would return. As the pitter-patter of monsoon season enveloped Elmond, there was an eerie lack of news about Michele's father.
After an uncountable number of days, the rain gradually died down, and Michele finally received a call from the Sentinel Bureau. The voice on the phone spoke about how someone had brought great harm to her father - he had fallen victim to the dreaded collapse syndrome. Immediately after, all of his duties were suspended.
Michele has always held firm in the belief that her father was relieved from his duties because of injury, but that didn't mean she didn't hear the constant flurry of rumors.
In Superheroes of Justice, the heroes are wounded before they can achieve justice - just as her father was during his mission.
Through the glass window of the hospital ward, Michele kept her watch day after day, but her father showed no sign of improving.
On the face of the girl who had always been so full of energy and sunshine, raindrops began to form.
RoleBiography.12804_StoryContent:
As she investigated the “strange behavior” of her partner, Lawine inadvertently touched upon a secret taboo.
Lawine dove deeper into the mystery, assisted along the way by her boss, Meredith, who herself had long-held suspicions about the organization. As they peeled the layers of the onion, they eventually learned about P.U.S' dark nature.
The truth was hard to believe. But it had crossed a line. Lawine knew that she would no longer be able to draw her blade for P.U.S.
Lawine and Meredith concluded that the public had to know the truth, but P.U.S executives had grown wise to what was going on. A group of assassins was already heading their way.
Amid her escape, Lawine came face-to-face with her partner once more - this time as enemies.
To Lawine's surprise, her partner showed no hesitation. A gunshot sounded, and as a cold bullet shattered Lawine's blade, the warm thread of their friendship was abruptly severed.
Officially branded as a defector, Lawine moved to the edges of society. With Meredith's help, she came into contact with an organization known as The Scissors.
Casting away her original name, she blended into the night. She resolved to bring the fight to P.U.S. Lawine would disappear, but a new face on the front lines would take her place.
RoleBiography.10103_StoryContent:
Immediately after graduating from the Investigator's Academy, Michele took the P.U.S Investigator Exam. During the practical examination, she often acted in ways that seemed contrary to common sense and confounded the examiners.
She completed the exam at lightning speed but received many warnings from the exam supervisor in the process.
Sure that she had bombed the exam, the frustrated Michele returned home with the face of a dirty tabby cat.
Just when the young girl thought she had missed out on her dream of becoming a hero, her father gave her the good news. She had passed, and he even brought her a gift to celebrate - two robo battlecats.
The battlecats, once her father's recon bots, had been upgraded to serve as tactical bots for Michele. She quickly gave them appropriate names: “Mighty Meow” and “Pawtector.”
Inspired by her favorite game, Michele's bold and unexpected antics quickly built her a reputation amongst her peers. Her “gamer's attitude” made her stick out like a sore thumb, and she was often reprimanded and ostracized for violating discipline.
“So much for being a hero's daughter...”
“Undisciplined investigators are an embarrassment!”
These voices of doubt and scorn surrounded Michele, planting a small seed of insecurity in the new investigator's heart.
RoleBiography.12401_StoryContent:
For as long as she can remember, Kokona had always been all by herself.
It was never her parents' intention for her to experience such a lonely childhood, but in the years before the great migration to Strinova, the two renowned scholars were needed in every reach of Earth to preserve a record of humanity's cultural heritage. It was a cause to which they dedicated their lives.
The young Kokona did not understand the great undertaking shouldered by her parents, nor did she understand the concepts of “solitude” or “loneliness” - no, it would be more accurate to say that she simply did not feel lonely.
Even in her small home, there was always something new to explore.
The first time she dressed herself, the first time she took a bath, the first time she made breakfast, and, of course, the first time she blew up the pressure cooker...
Each and every one of these firsts opened a whole new world to Kokona.
A born explorer, she faced every mystery in her world with a heart of pure curiosity.
But... She could never tell herself a bedtime story. The person who told the story wasn't supposed to fall asleep.
When she thought of this, the young Kokona felt a hint of loneliness for the first time.
RoleBiography.10502_StoryContent:
As the only child of Bruno Grove, Audrey followed her parents into the world of business when she reached her teens.
With a storied history spanning hundreds of years, the Grove family held an intricate network of interests that spanned banking, securities, auto manufacturing, energy, and many other fields.
Audrey's next challenge was her legacy's business empire - both its glory and its darkness.
As she entered the business world, Audrey faced a constant barrage of slander and accusations from her competitors, greatly damaging her trust in people. She soon realized that the only way to survive was to rely on family and family alone.
Owing to the great deal of experience she obtained in her formative years, Audrey soon became her father's second-in-command, always by his side in every family meeting.
Adorned in glorious attire, the girl socialized with many who bore her name - though she knew that people's hearts were unpredictable, deep down, she still held a glimmer of hope for familial affection.
“Audrey, happy coming-of-age! I'm sure greater gifts will await you in the future!”
Those were the words of blessing from Audrey's own uncle, Blaise Grove.
As Audrey clinked her glass against her uncle's as a show of respect, she looked forward to that gift with sincerity.
She would never have predicted the conspiracy lurking behind the corner.
RoleBiography.12803_StoryContent:
Since she joined the Sentinel Bureau, Lawine was always first in the office and last to leave. Her mission performance was no different - a record of excellence. The Bureau gave her a sense of purpose, and Lawine felt it was only right that she give her all in return.
“Justice, Bravery, Perseverance! We fight to protect this beautiful utopia!” The investigator's vow drove Lawine. It became the reason she drew her blade.
As the toll of each mission built up, Lawine's trusty practice sword became damaged beyond repair. The damage did not go unnoticed. It wasn't long before her chatterbox of a partner presented her with a new blade.
“To celebrate the first anniversary of Investigator Lawine's appointment...”
“And check it out... I've got one too! It's a set!
Lawine didn't really care. She was more concerned with when the next mission would start. That said... She couldn't bring herself to refuse her partner's warm invitation. On their next rest day, the two met again under Komos Tower to watch the sunset.
Lawine thought that those days would last forever...
But at some point, that chatterbox started acting “strangely,” and an undercurrent of danger returned to the investigator's peaceful life.
She would never have imagined that, despite having eliminated countless threats in P.U.S' name, she would one day receive the same mark.
RoleBiography.14604_StoryContent:
A few visitors offered Celestia a glimmer of hope: Urbino's new healthcare arm was making a new round of investments.
If she could find a way to get Urbino to buy into her “Consciousness Restoration” project, funding would no longer be a concern - at least in the short term.
These visitors had been former patients of hers. When they started showing mild signs of Collapse Syndrome, Celestia was able to intervene in time and tether their consciousness to reality.
If they were willing to come forward to prove the efficacy of her treatment, she was sure that Urbino would give her the funding she needed.
The recommendation of a former patient got her foot through the door, and negotiations proved short and sweet. For the first time, Celestia's project had received formal recognition.
During negotiations, Celestia visited Urbino's HQ (she would return there many times in the future) and was invited to take a look at their Multiverse Project.
For whatever reason, she didn't feel any interest in participating. To this day, she still dutifully watches over her restored Astral Sanctuary, living a silent but busy life.
RoleBiography.12805_StoryContent:
The Scissors are united by a common love for their old home and shared beliefs. Here, Lawine found the tranquility of her old home and a new reason to fight. She now raised her blade for a new purpose - to cut through falsehoods.
But that didn't mean that everything had changed. Lawine was still as excellent a soldier as ever, following orders to a tee. “Orders come first” became her motto.
Only those who grew exceptionally close to Lawine would be able to catch a glimpse at the myriad wounds under her bright red armor - each telling the tale of a different battle.
Lawine had long gotten used to the pain. Every wound was the same. Just patch it up and return to the fight. Her teammates fared much better. In fact, Lawine had a habit of putting herself between them and harm's way.
“When are you going to take care of yourself for a change?!” Ming was growing worried.
Even the sharpest blade dulls with time. In countless long and lonely nights, the image of Lawine's old partner lingered in her mind, confusing her heart in battle.
She remembered the words of her mother, who said that nature calms the mind. As orchids grow and flowers bloom, they symbolize new opportunities.
Lawine asked an acquaintance for a bag of orchid seeds and planted them in her home, holding the secret hope for a miracle.
The orchids did not grow. The troubled Lawine figured that the conditions were probably just too harsh.
But, ever since she met that person, the seeds suddenly began to sprout...
RoleBiography.10504_StoryContent:
As the region's commercial capital, Neutroville is home to a variety of magnificent and awe-inspiring skyscrapers. But Audrey knows she will someday build an even more majestic skyscraper - one adorned with the Grove unicorn.
Her path forward was destined to be a lonely one. Though many Groves were still willing to follow Audrey, she could no longer trust any of them.
Audrey's first order of business in Neutroville was to set up a luxury shopping mall, and as she established connections, she soon entered into a partnership with a powerful business alliance known as Urbino. Soon after, the Grove family had firmly established its roots in Neutroville.
When it came to her family, Audrey was now all business. Among them, she quickly gained a reputation for being domineering, cold as ice, and intimidating.
No one could deny her talent. When it came to discussions about the next leader of the Grove family, Audrey's name sounded like a chorus. Audrey couldn't care less - she remembered what they did to her father.
But the pressures of the cut-throat world of business and her constant vigilance finally took its toll on Audrey, taking shape in a terrible illness.
As she was rushed to the hospital, the last thing Audrey saw were tears streaming down the eyes of her parents and a bunch of strangers who bore her name.
From the depths of her heart, she screamed. “Don't trust those people. They aren't worthy.”
As her body finally gave in, she closed her eyes.
RoleBiography.10102_StoryContent:
In Superheroes of Justice, the two protagonists are often at odds with a gang of phantom thieves and a rogue's gallery of villains under the command of an ancient dragon.
The villains that Michele encountered in these battles, from The Burglar in Disguise and The Chainsaw Murderer to a mysterious creep known only as “Frankenstein,” all had a familiar feeling to them. They all seemed based on criminals that her father had brought to justice.
On a fateful afternoon, Michele was surfing the Superheroes of Justice forums for help on a particularly tricky level when she happened upon a post discussing the inspiration behind one of the protagonists, Big Meow.
The post gave a rigorous argument as to why the inspiration behind Big Meow was George Lee, an investigator with countless tricky cases under his belt. All the posters were heaping praise upon this legendary hero.
At that very moment, a deep desire was born in Michele's heart.
That night, when Michele's father returned from his mission as he had many times before, the young girl gazed upon his heroic uniform and shining metal, pledging, “I will become a hero of justice, just like you!”
As her father patted her forehead affectionately, he sensed that his little girl had grown up.
RoleBiography.10701_StoryContent:
On Maddelena Leary's seventh birthday, her parents, both artists themselves, presented her with a custom palette.
It was the first birthday gift she had received in her life. Young Maddelena named the palette “Kaleidoscope,” dreaming of all the colors she could fill it with.
When she painted with Kaleidoscope, the typically serious expression on her parents' faces was washed away by a look of rare happiness - it was one that the girl cherished greatly.
Maddelena resolved that she would dedicate herself to art. She wanted to create that same expression in others.
The Learys were a stern couple. Maddelena and her sister Galatea were required to spend every day in grueling practice, from six in the morning to nine at night.
As her palette grew more and more colorful, Maddelena's face and palms often became stained with paint, and the girl started to resemble a shabby cat.
Unlike Maddelena, her sister grew dissatisfied with their planned-out lives. During the day, Galatea would either be missing or returning home with strange, wriggling “materials,” while at night, she would suddenly appear out of nowhere like a ghost. These antics delivered no shortage of frights to poor Maddelena.
Nevertheless, Maddelena covered for her sister when she could, protecting Galatea from their parents' questioning.
In this way, Maddelena developed a habit of being helpful to those around her. Whenever she was out collecting materials for her art, she would always try to help those she encountered. It wasn't long before she had earned high esteem among her neighbors.
For this innocent girl, it seemed that making others happy was enough.
RoleBiography.12405_StoryContent:
With less than a month left before she had to defend her dissertation, Kokona finally drew up the design draft to transform Mister Sea Bunny into a medbot.
To get to this point, Kokona had gone through the trouble of learning medicine from scratch and even earned a medical certificate.
With the help of the school robotics club, Kokona modified and debugged Mister Sea Bunny just in time for her defense.
With no time to prepare any kind of speech, the girl stumbled through her defense and waited anxiously for the teacher's verdict.
The result? She had the highest score in her entire cohort.
“You've done amazingly, Kokona. But are you really not going to stay on as my teaching assistant?”
Kokona expressed her thanks but was firm in her choice.
“I've made my decision. I'm going to work hard with this child and bring his abilities to those who need them most.”
————
The memories of youth always make one wistful. Kokona was no different. Recalling those days, she always smiles with a knowing expression.
“Kokona! What's got you so happy?”
“Wanna hear the story? Once we're done with work, I'll tell you over some barbeque skewers.”
RoleBiography.14601_StoryContent:
To Celestia, her mother was like a guiding star - one whose expectations always P.U.Shed her to do better. Celestia was the same to her mother, who did her best to be a strong role model. She worked selflessly and tirelessly, all to ensure that Celestia had the brightest future possible. This was her dream, her greatest desire.
The young Celestia saw her mother as a smart and powerful woman. Though busy, she always spared time to ensure her daughter was walking on the right path. Benefitting from her mother's hard work, Celestia could find her interests earlier than her peers, received a quality education, and had far more freedom to decide who she wanted to become.
When Celestia first showed interest in the vast universe above, her mother took her to one of the largest observatories run by P.U.S, her employer.
As she gazed at her daughter doing her best to make sense of the precision instruments with her self-taught skills, Celestia's mother uttered the words the girl would remember for the rest of her life...
“Celestia, you must become the star that shines brightest in the night sky.”
The next years were a blur. Under her mother's watchful eye, Celestia started school, skipped a grade, entered university, graduated ahead of schedule with excellent grades, and finally entered P.U.S.
That same year, the first signs of The Collapse reared their heads.
RoleBiography.10105_StoryContent:
Those who ridiculed and questioned her and those who slandered and spread rumors about her father - their cacophony never ceased.
The heavy rain that stole her father away never seemed to end.
The young girl spent what felt like an eternity wading through helplessness and confusion.
In times like these, Michele would always hide away in her “secret base.” But on an ordinary rainy day, she found that her beloved cat cafe was closed, and she ended up wandering the streets alone.
Suddenly, she heard a soft meow sounded - two robocats were calling to her. They had searched far and wide for their long-lost owner in the freezing round. As she turned to the source of the sound, she saw them hunched on the ground, their batteries about to give out.
As Michele squatted down, the robocats put their mechanical paws on her reached-out hand, emanating a pulse of warmth that she had not felt in a long time.
It's as if a fire started in her palm. As the seconds passed by, more and more warmth rushed in.
Ever since she moved from a member of the reserves to an officially certified investigator, Michele's strong personality and unwillingness to admit defeat had attracted a group of precious comrades.
With each passing day, the rain let up a bit more until, finally, a beam of warm sunshine pierced its way through the clouds.
Just what kind of investigator should she be? And what was the truth behind what happened to her father?
The young girl's heart is still troubled by these questions...
In the sequel to Superheroes of Justice, Pawtector sets off on a new adventure, even without Mighty Meow by their side. Michele knew she had to do the same thing - she had to move forward.
She would only find the answer to these questions by meeting the future with a smile!
RoleBiography.10505_StoryContent:
As melodious notes wrapped her in a warm embrace, the amnesiac girl awoke from her dark slumber.
Opening her eyes, she saw a couple sitting nearby and a girl around her age playing the violin in the distance. But these warm notes quickly faded into the distance.
“Who are you?” asked the confused girl.
“We... We're your family,” the couple replied.
From the glass window, she saw many others outside her room, all wearing a unicorn badge. It seemed like a big family.
A personal stereo, a bone china coffee cup, and the hardcover edition of “The Many Discourses...” It's said that these items are “Audrey's” most prized possessions.
With “Audrey's things” in her hands, she visited relatives and friends alike, constantly searching for fragments of “Audrey's” memories. The journey was long and arduous, but she pressed on.
When the girl recovered, she only grew more dedicated to her work. She shouldered the responsibility of protecting her entire family and even resolved to run for leadership of Urbino.
Though the frustrations of her former life returned, things seemed different this time. And, of course, there was no shortage of gossip about her return from within the family's halls.
Can a broken mirror be restored? Was this “Audrey” pieced back together from a thousand disparate memories really the same person?
She felt as if she was trapped in a fairy tale. An animal lost in a forest without a single friend in the world.
If only she could follow that warm song and find her way out of the dark forest... The girl locked this wish deep within her heart.
RoleBiography.12801_StoryContent:
Having studied the art of budō with her father from a young age, it was only natural that Lawine inherited the mantle of his teachings.
For ten years, she's been honing her skills with the blade. She and the bamboo that grows in the dojo courtyard share an unspoken bond. Each bamboo carries the mark of her blade - they've been her training partners since they were just little saplings.
As she grew older, Lawine's blade became as sharp as the wind. With a single breath, she could cut through bamboo leaves like a hot knife through butter. Her skills became legendary among the dojo's disciples. Even working together, they were no match for her.
But Lawine never grew complacent. She would continue honing herself, day after day. Perhaps she thought of herself as a blade - in need of constant sharpening.
During the days of old Earth, Lawine had a singular focus - budō. She immersed herself in a world where only the reflection of her blade and the shadow of her target were real. Her only contact with the outside world was her parents. From this, she developed a reserved and taciturn character.
Much was said about Lawine by the other disciples. “A poor, lonely child.” “A strange fool whose only friend is her sword.” But she didn't care about that. The only sound that mattered to her was the gentle rustling of bamboo leaves.
The wind has picked up once more. Shadows sway through the courtyard. Just listen to the wind, and be firm when you draw!
RoleBiography.14603_StoryContent:
No matter her reasons, her actions were a direct rebellion against her mother's years of care and direction. But faced with the outbreak of suffering, the limitations of academic research, her anxiety over her lack of action, and even her ignorance about the universe...
Celestia was unable to summon an answer from the depths of her heart. Perhaps these feelings would have to co-exist together.
And so Celestia left P.U.S and her mother's side.
Based on her practical experience in identifying and treating patients of The Collapse, Celestia came up with the “consciousness restoration” project. Soon after, she set out to use her savings to open the Astral Sanctuary and began helping patients with nowhere else to turn.
But with all that said, why did she, who was always far more interested in astronomy and cosmology, suddenly decide to devote herself to such work? Celestia tended to be the one with all the answers, yet this question bugged her for quite some time.
Every now and then, Celestia could hear a voice questioning her from her heart.
...
A year later, lacking the funds to keep going, the Astral Sanctuary had shut.
RoleBiography.12802_StoryContent:
As calamity struck old Earth, the Lawine dojo became barren as its disciples fended for their lives. Lawine's parents did not fare any better, claimed by the worst cold snap the world had ever seen.
Lawine became a wasteland wanderer. Lost and aimless, she had no idea what the next day would bring.
“Strinova will be humanity's new home. A land of infinite possibilities. One with no poverty, suffering, division, or exploitation...” These broadcasts played incessantly in old Earth's run-down streets.
A new home? Lawine had lost hers long ago.
One after another, the desperate masses pinned their hopes on this “new world.” An influx of refugees started flooding into Strinova. With nothing left on old Earth, Lawine threw herself in with their lot.
Lawine's nimbleness and skill with a blade earned her a place in the Sentinel Bureau. She would serve as an investigator under Painting Utopia Security.
During her time at P.U.S, she made acquaintances with a chatty colleague who seemed to be the opposite of her in every way. That person had a penchant for issuing challenges, and no matter how many times Lawine would defeat them, they would always be up for another round. Though quite troublesome, the truth was that Lawine didn't mind her that much.
“Let's see who can reach the objective first!”
Challenge 2614. Another win for Lawine.
“Look! The sunset! It feels so warm...”
By the time Lawine collected herself, the sunset had already completely enveloped them.
Something seemed to have changed in her. As Lawine stared into the distance, she felt that she had found a new home.
RoleBiography.10702_StoryContent:
The Elitron School of Arts, known colloquially as ESA, had a sterling reputation for creating stars out of its students. Having the sisters make it into the school had been the Learys' greatest ambition.
When Galatea got into ESA without even sitting the exam based on a recommendation, Maddelena resolved that she wouldn't lose out to her sister.
Looking to improve her chances, Maddelena signed up for a training camp known in equal part for its grueling difficulty and prestige amongst admissions officers.
Thinking back on those days, Maddelena can only recall that she was so tired that she nearly drank a cup of paint for breakfast. Her dreams were filled with dancing lights and shapes taking form.
But at least her hard work paid off. She was able to get into ESA with the same admission scores.
On the day she bid farewell to her parents, Maddelena felt an emptiness inside. It was her first time studying so far away from home.
She made a special point of taking her cherished palette along with her.
Maddelena's new and unfamiliar school life was a source of much discomfort.
She became frazzled - her semesters filled with embarrassing mistakes like handing in her oil painting homework during sketching class and arriving at swimming class in her sculpting class uniform.
“How could a genius like Galatea be the sister of such a klutz?” Maddelena was nothing like what people expected.
As tales of her mishaps spread across the school, she earned herself a new reputation among the students - “that girl's klutzy sister.”
After each fast-paced and chaotic day, Maddelena would always hide away in her dorm, staring at an unfamiliar ceiling, lost in a trance.
RoleBiography.12404_StoryTitle: Do Androids Dream of Electric Sheep?
RoleBiography.10704_StoryContent:
Following her graduation, Maddelena busied herself with submitting her art to museums and magazines, hoping to expand her reach.
As Maddelena labored away, Galatea's star continued to rise - even appearing on Urbino's most popular art program, The Hand of Leonardo, making a name for herself with her charming demeanor and sharp opinions.
Maddelena never liked those kinds of programs. Still, she heard much about her sister from those around her.
Even though Maddelena continued to work hard, the responses she received were muted. Whenever she and Galatea submitted designs to the same competition, she would always lose.
The Windy Town Improvisation Competition, the ESA Alumni Competition, and so many more... Her defeats were too numerous to count.
“You've stayed curled up in your cage like a bird without wings - that's why no one's opening their doors to you!”
Her sister's shouts lingered in Maddelena's ears like a distant echo.
The brighter Galatea shined, the more Maddelena felt her light dimmed.
As grains of frustration and confusion filled her heart, she lost the will to return her parent's calls. Eventually, she didn't even dare to return home.
Without telling her parents, Maddelena set out as a freelance artist, drifting along the art world and taking inspiration from nature.
She developed a motto to guide her journey, “designers are either in the process of creation or the process of inspiration.”
It's said that traces of her can be found in every corner of Strinova.
RoleBiography.12402_StoryTitle: The Story of Mister Sea Bunny
RoleBiography.10705_StoryContent:
Though Maddelena's career was rocky, her eureka moments still made the occasional splash.
The problem - they're all sparks of improvisation, usually from when Maddelena gets a blessing in disguise or when she's helping someone else.
“Lisa Mona” was created with broken glass, while “Leaning Tower of Pisa” came from helping a neighbor cut their window grills.
Some of Maddelena's inspired designs led to a rush of bookings from her neighbors, while others were even showcased in the creative works areas of local museums.
With the help of some luck, Maddelena was able to secure a string of orders - enough to keep her comfortable as a freelancer.
All the while, she continued to enjoy the small pleasures of helping out those around her.
But the calls from home did not stop, and she eventually had to give in. At the urging of her parents, Maddelena took a job as a painter at Cloudscape Gallery.
Rumors had it that the museum was owned by a Urbino bigshot - someone who went by the name of Bai.
The work was basic and tedious. Cloudscape Gallery was hardly a challenge for her skills.
As a result of her post, Maddelena was once again exposed to the media of the art world and, inevitably, her sister's continued stardom.
“If only I could shine so brightly...”
With a hint of defiance, Maddelena looked down on Kaleidoscope palette, imagining it was filled with her own vivid colors...
RoleBiography.10703_StoryContent:
Maddelena developed a habit of laughing off everything at school, no matter the nicknames or gossip.
Redoubling her efforts in her studies, she was able to barely maintain above-average grades.
As Maddelena's graduation project neared, many of her proposals were rejected by her instructors. Seeking help, she sought out Galatea, who had already graduated.
Maddelena showed Galatea sister over thirty carefully designed sketches with the genuine hope that her sister would be able to understand and appreciate her designs.
But all she got was a cold response,
“These designs shouldn't count as art at all.”
Galatea was always straight to the point. Her words weren't intended to sting, but how could they not?
Maddelena immediately asked if she could see Galatea's designs. When she was given a bunch of scraggly lines and circles with no clear meaning (some sketches were even blank!), she only grew more confused.
“Do you mean... that these count as art?”
“Then what should? Those sketches of yours that no one gives a second look? Do you have any idea how many Dream Tokens the auction house has valued these at?”
“Sister, art can't be measured in Dream Tokens...”
“You're still as naive as ever. You've stayed curled up in your cage like a bird without wings - that's why no one's opening their doors to you!”
The atmosphere grew tense enough to cut with a knife. The sisters continued to bicker until their parents finally intervened.
Maddelena has long forgotten how their fight ended.
She and Galatea returned to their old equilibrium. Galatea would show her beautiful hats while she would express exasperation at Galatea's strange designs.
But ever since that fight, Maddelena found that her sister spent far less time at home. Galatea would often disappear or drop out of contact without so much as a warning.
She had no idea where Galatea would go, but she could tell something had changed. An invisible barrier was standing between Maddelena, Galatea, and their family.
RoleBiography.14602_StoryContent:
First came a localized wave of confusion and delirium reported by medical check-ups in residential areas. As the responsible agency, P.U.S attached great importance to the reports and promptly assigned personnel to assist.
But these efforts bore few results. As the medical community was still locked in debate, the outbreak of The Collapse began.
As a member of P.U.S, Celestia had been part of the relief team but found herself just as helpless in the face of The Collapse as her colleagues.
The appearance of The Scissors only worsened the situation as they lit a fire under all the contradictions of this “new world.”
Her heart, confused by all that had unfolded, Celestia turned to her mother, who was now a high-level P.U.S executive, for help. The answer she received? Delve deeper into the latest cutting-edge studies and operational management techniques. Being distracted and worrying about the unimportant was the last thing she wanted for Celestia.
Go on, and shine like the brightest star!

RoleSkin.20146201_TskinDescription:
【"Have you ever truly gazed at the starry sky?”
“I heard there is a unique star for everyone, waiting alone in the universe, hoping someone would gaze at it.”
“If one day you discover a different kind of light while gazing at the sky, that's probably your star blinking at you.”
“Where is my star? Well... that's a secret.”

The girl never stops her pursuit of the night sky.
On countless nights of gazing at the starlight, the girl patiently waits for the one star in the vast galaxy that captures her light.
One, the star blinks at her.
And the entire night colors its colors.】
RoleSkin.20146206_TskinDescription:
【The rose royal swordswoman gazes into the distance.
She sees nothing but carnage and rivers of blood.
The rose-decorated sword pierces an enemy's heart.
The rose is dyed in blood's hue; shadows cast wide their pall.
My mind, like the breeze, wanders far, unconfined by any wall.
“For you alone, the flowers unveil their bloom; should they fade, what sorrow calls?”】

She sees nothing but carnage and rivers of blood.

The rose is dyed in blood's hue; shadows cast wide their pall.
My mind, like the breeze, wanders far, unconfined by any wall.

RoleSkin.20101105_Description:
In stark contrast to her usual authoritative demeanor, Michele becomes a mischievous demon straight out of a fairy tale.

【Someone is knocking on the door.
“Open up. It's Investigator Michele from the underworld. I'm here to inspect your snack reserve today!”
Donning this outfit, Michele appears happier than usual.
But she's still herself. So, it should be fine, right?】
RoleSkin.20108101_Description:
Nobunaga's Painting Utopia Security special operations combat uniform. Under the steel and leather, his elegant and calm demeanor remains undiminished.

【“Activate remote control and the radar system. Do not leave anything behind.”
Under Nobunaga's command, a meticulous raid is underway.
However, the operation ended before it even began.
“You're the suspect, aren't you? Are you going to surrender, or are you going to make me do it?”】
RoleSkin.20101051_Description:
Eager to participate in the Port Euler Motorboat Grand Prix, Michele has a customized racing suit made.
Three, two, one... Go!
RoleSkin.20124001_Description: Kokona's fully functional customized sniper combat uniform with a modest design, suitable for all weather conditions.
RoleSkin.20133053_Description: A special outfit customized for Meredith. The diamond core symbolizes her resolution - sharp, rational, and unwavering.
RoleSkin.20109002_Description: A variant of Reiichi's combat uniform. The mysterious purple envelops his deep concern.
RoleSkin.20109001_Description: Reiichi's favorite outfit. It is comfortable, simple, practical, and reliable, exuding the firm will of a warrior.
RoleSkin.20109106_Description:
Reiichi's special gear for infiltrating the black market, emphasizing the mysterious charm and personal style of the East. The pendant is crafted from waste stone. Although it is not a genuine antique, it looks real enough to the untrained eye.

【“Heh... You've got a good eye. This is top-notch stuff.”】
RoleSkin.20107104_Description:
A space-themed white bodysuit featuring stylish black mechanical rabbit ears, making Maddelena seem less simple and more daring than usual.

【“Look! Doesn't the reflection of this outfit resemble moonlight?”
“I heard that a bunny lived happily on the Moon. Could there be an electronic bunny on Strinova's moon as well?”
The girl happily dreams of space under the cover of the night.】
RoleSkin.20105053_Description: An elegant outfit inspired by playing cards. Hearts, diamonds, spades, and clubs... As for the Joker, that is Audrey herself.
RoleSkin.20131003_Description: Yvette's spare lab coat. Beneath her cold exterior, there lies a fiery heart.
RoleSkin.20131102_Description:
Yvette's beach outfit that highlights her eye-catching vitality and coolness, making her look like a cute panda.

【“Pandas... do not appear on the beach.”
Of course, Yvette knows this.
But then again, why did she pick this outfit? You can't help but wonder.
“...In that case, I'll be truly unique.”】
RoleSkin.20131001_Description: Yvette's favorite lab coat. The pair of bear ears on the hood reveals her childlike innocence.
RoleSkin.20110102_Description:
Rumor has it that there is a highly skilled young man who shows up in the auto shop from time to time. No matter what the malfunction is or the age of a race car, as long as he repairs and tunes it, the vehicle's performance will be enhanced. Everyone praises his repair skills, but few inquire about his identity - this is exactly what he aims to achieve.

【“Check out the repair. There's nothing my wrench can't fix.”
“However, the parts are severely worn. You gotta take care of your car, man.”
“...You think you've seen me somewhere else? Well, it's a large city. Perhaps you have; perhaps you haven't. Don't overthink it.”】
RoleSkin.20108007_Description: Nobunaga's spare work outfit. The rust does not hide his lofty ambition.
RoleSkin.20124054_Description: A work outfit similar to that of a taxi driver, yet exceptionally striking because of the wearer. Kokona says it is her disguise, but is that really the case?
RoleSkin.20146206_Description: An outfit in the style of a knight's armor. Beneath the elegance and splendor, there lies a brave soul.
RoleSkin.20146207_Description: An outfit in the style of a knight's armor. Beneath the elegance and splendor, there lies a brave soul.
RoleSkin.20146208_Description: An outfit in the style of a knight's armor. Beneath the elegance and splendor, there lies a brave soul.
RoleSkin.20146209_Description: An outfit in the style of a knight's armor. Beneath the elegance and splendor, there lies a brave soul.
RoleSkin.20146210_Description: An outfit in the style of a knight's armor. Beneath the elegance and splendor, there lies a brave soul.
RoleSkin.20133103_Description:
The outfit Meredith wears while performing for displaced children at a charity event in Preton. Despite her expressionless face, the magician is still loved by the children.

【“Magic is but a quantitative technique, after all.”】
RoleSkin.20105001_Description: A mercenary outfit designed by Audrey, integrating her love for glamor into the noble aesthetics inherited from her mother.
RoleSkin.20105002_Description: A variant of Audrey's mercenary outfit. Her unchanging will is as steadfast as the green mountain.
RoleSkin.20107054_Description: This childish blueberry milk outfit suits Maddelena perfectly. After all, only with the heart of a child can one create true beauty.
RoleSkin.20105103_Description:
The girl's graceful figure resembles a willow with fine branches, her elegant gauze dress fluttering in the wind. Dressed as a classical dancer, Audrey exudes an indescribable exotic charm with her every move.

【The guqin strums beneath Dragon Gate's shadowed boughs. Jade pots pour wine, crystal-clear and bright.
Together we drink, as colors shift above. From vermilion to jade, in the glow of our love.
Faces flushed with the joy of the moment's embrace. The fair lady's laughter, a flower's grace.
Why not revel till we're lost in the night's sweet thrum? If not now, when will we ever find our way home?】
RoleSkin.20128104_Description:
Beneath the flamboyant style of the combat uniform, there lies Lawine's calm and rational heart. Hiding in the shadows, eliminate the enemy with a single strike.

【A shadow dashes swiftly in the city at nightfall.
No one sees here. No one hears her.
“You let your guard down... And now I've succeeded.”
Lawine, the Third Executor of The Scissors, once again strikes the enemy of her faith.】
RoleSkin.20124104_Description:
A piece of outdoor gear modified by Kokona. Originally intended for exploration, it has been transformed into a ceremonial outfit suitable for outings and picnics. Speaking of which, the strawberries on the outfit seem to be editable.

【“If you're interested, feel free to have a bite.”】
RoleSkin.20124002_Description: Kokona's spare sniper combat uniform. The light pink lifts the spirits.
RoleSkin.20115101_Description:
I invited Flavia to go out with me. To my surprise, she actually said yes.

【“What is it? The weather's nice. The butterfly needs to sunbathe as well.”】
RoleSkin.20128007_Description: Lawine's spare combat uniform in blue, resembling the silent cold night.
RoleSkin.20108001_Description: A special uniform belonging to Nobunaga, captain of the first squad of the Sentinel Bureau. The meticulous design reflects his strict professional attitude.
RoleSkin.20132055_Description: Ming's race car driver's outfit, incorporating her favorite racing elements. Behind wheels, she turns into a blue whirlwind, becoming the swiftest presence on the track.
RoleSkin.20132001_Description: Ming's combat uniform. The seemingly combination balances practicality and aesthetics, suitable for both combat and daily life.
RoleSkin.20132006_Description: Ming's spare combat uniform in orange and red, resembling like the afterglow of a spectacular sunset.
RoleSkin.20146001_Description: Celestia wears this dress while working at Astral Sanctuary. Its twinkling star patterns symbolize Astral Sanctuary's creed of not giving up on any patient.
RoleSkin.20146201_Description: Celestia only puts on this loungewear when resting. Only those closest to her have a chance to see her in this outfit.
RoleSkin.20146005_Description: Celestia's spare work uniform in lime green, showcasing her charm.
RoleSkin.20112101_Description:
The outfit is inspired by hunters who once roamed the forests at night. Its bizarre design embodies the tension of the era.

【“Come on, Fuchsia. You're the only one left! The Nightstalker suits you perfectly!”
“This outfit is not suitable for carrying out missions.”
“Live a little, would you? Let's go. Photo time!”
“Uh... fine.”

Having heard her companions' teasing, Fuchsia remains silent for a long time. She knows it is all in jest and that no matter how her attire changes, her past cannot not be altered.
Yet for some reason, she feels a long-lost sense of warmth in her heart.】
RoleSkin.20128051_Description: As the maple leaves fall, the interwoven red and white symbolizes Lawine's heart - once beautiful and pure, now tainted by the flames of war.
RoleSkin.20133006_Description: Meredith's spare combat uniform in red, matching the color of The Scissors. The rusty blade of yesteryear shall pave an iron path.
RoleSkin.20107003_Description: A special variant of Maddelena's painter's outfit. The tender pink resembles butterflies and blooming flowers.
RoleSkin.20133001_Description: A special combat uniform crafted with the cutting-edge technology of The Scissors, incorporating Meredith's lifetime of knowledge into its complex design.
RoleSkin.20110001_Description: Bai Mo wears this mercenary outfit when he is out on missions. The design emphasizes practicality while incorporating streetwear elements - sleek, carefree, unfettered.
RoleSkin.20110002_Description: Bai Mo's spare mercenary outfit, making him look like a teenager ready to start a joyful picnic.
RoleSkin.20131056_Description: Under the simple white and blue coat, the orange socks remind one of sweet soda. The usually introverted and shy Yvette occasionally shows such a sweet side.
RoleSkin.20107001_Description: A simple yet artistic painter's outfit. Rather than elaborate attire, Maddelena cares more about the harmony of colors.
RoleSkin.20101001_Description: Michele incorporates her favorite cat elements into her uniform, giving it a playful touch while maintaining the professionalism expected of a P.U.S investigator.
RoleSkin.20101008_Description: Michele's investigator uniform. Lightly dyed in khaki, it is simple and durable.
RoleSkin.20146053_Description: The candies adorn the dress with rainbow colors as her aura blooms in the summer. What color will the next rainbow candy be?
RoleSkin.20112056_Description: Fuchsia's disguise while working undercover at the café. Sharks may not enjoy coffee, but cups of rich caramel coffee warm the girl's frosty face.
RoleSkin.20112004_Description: Fuchsia's spare combat uniform. Demons come out at dusk, choosing their next victim.
RoleSkin.20112001_Description: A professional assassin's tight suit. Born for battle, its streamlined design is devoid of any superfluous elements.
RoleSkin.20115054_Description: Flavia's customized outfit. The viper lurks in the water, waiting for its thirsty prey. No, she is not the viper; she is the hunter waiting next to it.
RoleSkin.20115001_Description: Flavia's combat uniform with a simple and comfortable design, featuring an image of a butterfly to enhance the wearer's elegant charm.
RoleSkin.20115002_Description: Flavia's spare uniform. The wings of the butterfly flutter in the breeze, elusively moving closer and farther.
RoleSkin.20108051_Description: The black and blue electronic-style outfit featuring a disc-coated walkie-talkie adds a touch of fashion to the usually cold Nobunaga.
RoleSkin.20137052_Description: A performance costume featuring patterns of stars. The fluttering starlight resembles Kanami's gorgeous dance moves.
RoleSkin.20132101_Description:
A black outfit suitable for nighttime operations. It was originally intended to blend perfectly into the night, but at Ming's request, a touch of dark red was added, like a flame burning quietly - not dazzling, but never yielding. She will chase the night and drive it away.

【“Go home, kids. The night is my battlefield.”】
RoleSkin.20128001_Description: Lawine's highly special operations combat uniform adapted for The Scissors' active camouflage technology.
RoleSkin.20109053_Description: The white shirt makes Reiichi look like a physician. In fact, he is skilled only in emergency battlefield treatment. Everything he does is for victory.
RoleSkin.20110051_Description: A chef's outfit featuring patterns of fish and bamboo leaves, reminiscent of the aroma of sushi. To Bai Mo, freedom and delicacies are the two most significant things in life.
RoleSkin.20137055_Description: Kanami's performance costume for a coffee brand promotion event, specially designed with latte art in mind, conveying the warmth of coffee to the fans.
RoleSkin.20137105_Description:
The outfit Kanami wears when invited to the Golden Tree Symphony concert. The outfit showcases her charm and coordination with the conductor. Intentional, perhaps?

【“I would like to dream the most beautiful dream with you.”】
RoleSkin.20137003_Description: Kanami's spare performance costume in dazzling ochre, symbolizing the passionate flame in her heart.
RoleSkin.20137001_Description: Kanami's performance costume, combining beauty and practicality. The slender hems flutter in the wind like the wings of a nightingale.

RoleTeam.3_TeamDesc: These Strinovian from all walks of life have banded together to fight for their "own ideals."
RoleTeam.2_TeamDesc: Active in all parts of Strinova society, this mysterious organization is not to be underestimated. They are wary of the changes in Strinova World and hold a deep suspicion toward Dream Town.
RoleTeam.1_TeamDesc: Led by Sistine and made up of veteran agents and talented newcomers, PUS is dedicated to protecting the order and security of Dream Town.

RoleVoice.22137068_Content: The preparations are complete. My performance is about to begin!
RoleVoice.22110139_Content: Just a temporary setback... Let's try again.
RoleVoice.22115139_Content: One careless move loses the whole game.
RoleVoice.22101069_Content: Fight with me, and justice will be ours!
RoleVoice.22133137_Content:
Next time, I won't forgive such failure.
Do your best.
RoleVoice.22146137_Content: I won't let this happen again.
RoleVoice.22115073_Content: If you want to avoid being charmed, you will have to do more than just closing your eyes.
RoleVoice.22128112_Content: Do not sink into the darkness!
RoleVoice.22108139_Content: Get out of your comfort zone. To fail is to learn.
RoleVoice.22124138_Content: Good job. This victory was a team effort.
RoleVoice.22109073_VoiceName: Active skill: Turning a blind eye!
RoleVoice.22109073_VoiceNameShort: Active Skill: Turning a Blind Eye
RoleVoice.22131072_VoiceName: Active Skill: It's Up to You
RoleVoice.22131072_VoiceNameShort: Active Skill: It's Up to You
RoleVoice.22112074_VoiceName: Active skill: I know where you are
RoleVoice.22146066_Content: I'll always be here if you need me.
RoleVoice.22132067_Content: Even if I die today, I'll do so with no regrets.
RoleVoice.22108112_Content: You won't get away with it!
RoleVoice.22105113_Content: You are no match for me.
RoleVoice.22110109_Content: You are no match for me!
RoleVoice.22128074_Content: There is no escape for you.
RoleVoice.22110069_Content: Urbino has everything you desire, including freedom!
RoleVoice.22115077_Content: Can you guess which one is the real me?
RoleVoice.22105137_Content: Just you wait. I won't lose next time.
RoleVoice.22112020_Content: It's fine to use it occasionally.
RoleVoice.22131114_Content: Try as you might, the outcome remains the same.
RoleVoice.22105113_VoiceName: Elimination: You are no match for me!
RoleVoice.22105110_VoiceName: Elimination: Is that all you've got?
RoleVoice.22107114_VoiceNameShort: Elimination: Not So Strong, Are You?
RoleVoice.22128112_VoiceName: Elimination: Do not sink into the darkness
RoleVoice.22128113_VoiceName: Elimination: The world is not yours!
RoleVoice.22105079_Content: You will not escape the flames!
RoleVoice.22108129_Content: Don't worry. I will protect you.
RoleVoice.22115079_Content: Don't blink, lest you miss it.
RoleVoice.22115069_Content: To make the rules, you first have to understand them.
RoleVoice.22101067_Content: I will uphold the order of Strinova!
RoleVoice.22128139_Content: Was my best shot... just not enough?
RoleVoice.22110068_Content: As long as I'm still breathing, no one shall control Urbino!
RoleVoice.22105129_Content: I've saved you. Don't you forget it.
RoleVoice.22101137_Content: Damn it... I shouldn't have lost!
RoleVoice.22110137_Content: Damn it. I was this close!
RoleVoice.22115138_Content: A pleasure working with you, Navigator.
RoleVoice.22137066_Content: Listen up! The battlefield is my stage!
RoleVoice.22112068_Content: Just carry out missions as usual.
RoleVoice.22101140_Content: Humph. I knew I could do it!
RoleVoice.22124137_Content: Guh... I won't admit defeat. I've got to do better next time.
RoleVoice.22137072_Content: Shh! Don't let me find you!
RoleVoice.22115137_Content: All mortals are equal when we perish. That includes you and I.
RoleVoice.22137069_Content: Kanami will respond to the desires beneath the waves!
RoleVoice.22131139_Content:
Don't lose heart.
Fay says: “Failure is the mother of success.”
RoleVoice.22107139_Content:
It's alright, everyone!
We'll get 'em tomorrow!
RoleVoice.22124140_Content:
A decisive victory!
Didn't I say that a good medic is the key to every battle?
RoleVoice.22146139_Content: I failed... I have to keep improving my skills.
RoleVoice.22109137_Content: Failure is a necessary cost for innovation.
RoleVoice.22107140_Content: Okay... When inspiration strikes, one must answer!
RoleVoice.22131070_Content: This place is crowded... Fay is uncomfortable.
RoleVoice.22101139_Content: If only I fought a bit harder...
RoleVoice.22112138_Content: If there's a reward, taiyaki will do.
RoleVoice.22107073_Content: Watch and learn. This is how you paint!
RoleVoice.22128137_Content: Behind every failure is an opportunity to learn...
RoleVoice.22124139_Content: Even if I'm the only one left standing, I need to make sure that everyone can evacuate safely.
RoleVoice.22115112_Content: One ultimately has to awaken from the illusion.
RoleVoice.22101069_VoiceName: Deployment: Justice Never Fails to Show!
RoleVoice.22101069_VoiceNameShort: Deployment: Justice Never Fails to Show!
RoleVoice.22124079_Content: The reviver comes at light speed!
