RoleVoice.22133138_Content: We're one step closer to home.
RoleVoice.22105068_Content: What's the matter? You've never seen me all dressed up?
RoleVoice.22109069_Content: People need someone to blame, and I don't care if it's me.
RoleVoice.22110077_Content: Want to take me down? No way!
RoleVoice.22146074_Content: May you find happiness and love.
RoleVoice.22146138_Content: I hope this war will end soon... but until that day, I'll continue giving it my all!
RoleVoice.22132077_Content: I stand alone against you all!
RoleVoice.22115067_Content: I, too, am a piece on the board.
RoleVoice.22109140_Content: We are The Scissors. We come for innovation.
RoleVoice.22132138_Content: We are The Scissors. Our destiny is to overthrow this world!
RoleVoice.22108069_Content: I will keep my word, for this is my sole purpose.
RoleVoice.22105112_Content: You know I'll win, don't you?
RoleVoice.22133113_Content: I hear the gods comforting the dead.
RoleVoice.22115111_Content: You have no place under my rule.
RoleVoice.22133140_Content: I shall guide the way forward.
RoleVoice.22128140_Content: I'll never give up the will to fight!
RoleVoice.22109139_Content: I've given it my all, but it's still far from enough.
RoleVoice.22109068_Content: I pull the trigger only to welcome a new era.
RoleVoice.22999018_Content: We need 1 more kill to win
RoleVoice.22132137_Content: My faith will not be shaken!
RoleVoice.22108140_Content: My faith shall guide me to the end.
RoleVoice.22105066_Content: The best battlefield negotiator is a bullet!
RoleVoice.22115066_Content: The battlefield is like a chessboard.
RoleVoice.22105069_Content: Even in battle, one must maintain style!
RoleVoice.22110137_VoiceName: Defeat: So Close Yet So Far
RoleVoice.22110137_VoiceNameShort: Defeat: So Close Yet So Far
RoleVoice.22105074_VoiceName: Skill: Get out of my way!
RoleVoice.22107073_VoiceName: Skill: This is how you paint!
RoleVoice.22107073_VoiceNameShort: Skill: This Is How You Paint!
RoleVoice.22999020_Content: The enemy needs 5 more kills to win
RoleVoice.22131020_Content: Data shows that carrying a secondary weapon increases combat efficiency by 37%.
RoleVoice.22110066_Content: I got a new request already?
RoleVoice.22115114_Content: No matter how many times you try, you will lose.
RoleVoice.22109129_Content: No need to thank me. Continue with the mission.
RoleVoice.22105070_Content: Since you're here, try to achieve glory!
RoleVoice.22131067_Content: Let's get it over with. I have research to conduct.
RoleVoice.22115068_Content: Stars align like chess pieces, casting shadows of butterflies.
RoleVoice.22137802_Content: With your support, Kanami can't lose!
RoleVoice.22132068_Content: Come on, let's set the fires of resistance ablaze!
RoleVoice.22132078_Content: Here the roar of the rebel!
RoleVoice.22101111_Content: After all, we are on opposite sides...
RoleVoice.22112074_Content: Your scent gives away your position.
RoleVoice.22133073_Content: Behold the might of the sandstorm!
RoleVoice.22109077_Content: None shall escape from my gun!
RoleVoice.22112069_Content: Eliminate the enemies. Is that it?
RoleVoice.22101078_Content: Mighty Meow will not forgive you!
RoleVoice.22109070_Content: Born in the light, hidden in the darkness, such is a sniper's mission.
RoleVoice.22137070_Content: Compose the perfect melody with bullets!
RoleVoice.22124067_Content: Leave the medic work to me.
RoleVoice.22132139_Content: Put your faith in me, and I shall lead you into the light!
RoleVoice.22128079_Content: The truth is hidden among shadows!
RoleVoice.22137801_Content: When we're done here, make sure you check out my new song!
RoleVoice.22133114_Content: This is the end for you.
RoleVoice.22133139_Content:
Things have gone wrong.
We must analyze this defeat.
RoleVoice.22107079_VoiceName: Ultimate: I won't hold back anymore!
RoleVoice.22115140_Content: Cooperation among the wise maximizes advantages.
RoleVoice.22131129_Content: Fay will be rooting for you.
RoleVoice.22115078_Content: Life and death are but an impermanent illusion.
RoleVoice.22128068_Content: Wake up! You have a right to know the truth.
RoleVoice.22131138_Content: We won! Our job is done.
RoleVoice.22115070_Content: Follow the butterfly, then step into its trap.
RoleVoice.22115113_Content: Blindly trusting the beauty will cost you your life.
RoleVoice.22131140_Content: It's been a lucky day, right Fay?
RoleVoice.22101073_Content: It's my turn to protect everyone!
RoleVoice.22128077_Content: The destiny of this world is to be buried here.
RoleVoice.22128138_Content: This hypocritical world... should be overthrown.
RoleVoice.22137110_Content: This counts as a performance, too!
RoleVoice.22146140_Content: This was a real team effort.
RoleVoice.22137078_Content: This performance is prepared for you!
RoleVoice.22110140_Content: This is Urbino's path to freedom!
RoleVoice.22107072_Content: This is how you make art!
RoleVoice.22128020_Content: Will this weapon do the trick?
RoleVoice.22107020_Content: Will this weapon do the trick?
RoleVoice.22132140_Content: We are The Scissors. Remember us.

RuleAttribute.104012_Desc: Enables opening the Superstring Selection UI at any time. Changes take effect in the next round.
RuleAttribute.10402_Desc: Each time the player respawns a random superstring will be selected.

SequenceDialogue.9804021_TextContext: There's more than one group of AI guards. We need to eliminate them all, so don't let up!
SequenceDialogue.9801066_TextContext: Do you remember the Type P-4 bomb? We used it once in training.
SequenceDialogue.9804003_TextContext: ———— (cutting out) Lawine? Can you... hear me? Lawine?
SequenceDialogue.9800005_TextContext: A “utopia” where eternal life was possible, all thanks to the power of superstrings.
SequenceDialogue.9801050_TextContext: Oh no! The control center has been breached!
SequenceDialogue.9804030_TextContext: No. The enemy firepower is too dense. Evade and retreat.
SequenceDialogue.9804025_TextContext: Stay vigilant. There will be two more garages up ahead. Let's push on.
SequenceDialogue.9801044_TextContext: Since you have already made up your mind, stay true to yourself until collapse syndrome is cured.
SequenceDialogue.9801018_TextContext: Negative. The Komos Tower is heavily guarded. We'll split up this time.
SequenceDialogue.9801001_TextContext: I have waited for this moment for far too long. This is the only way now.
SequenceDialogue.9801002_TextContext: This is the only way now.
SequenceDialogue.9804006_TextContext: The power of P.U.S' defense system - you have to see it to believe it.
SequenceDialogue.9800003_TextContext: The wretched awaited rescue in the frozen wastes.
SequenceDialogue.9800007_TextContext: In this new era, humans became like gods.
SequenceDialogue.9801042_TextContext: With peace as the endpoint, this expedition will not be a short one.
SequenceDialogue.9801057_TextContext: Focus on your research, Yvette. Instructor Kokona and I will deal with The Scissors!
SequenceDialogue.9801078_TextContext: Yvette, The Scissors are after the crystals!
SequenceDialogue.9801029_TextContext: The uncontrollable collapse may damage the string sequence.
SequenceDialogue.9801032_TextContext: However, this experiment improved on past purification methods, isolating observers using a black box to prevent collapse.
SequenceDialogue.9801011_TextContext: Please put me out of my misery!
SequenceDialogue.9801076_TextContext: Continue working on the bomb. I'm going to support Yvette!
SequenceDialogue.9804029_TextContext: We'll come through the sides. Keep your eye out for any ambushes.
SequenceDialogue.9801051_TextContext: Must they come now of all times...
SequenceDialogue.9804018_TextContext: Excellent work, Lawine. Ahead of you is the Comos AI Garage. All the AI perimeter guards come from here. Ming will find a way to hijack the guards - that will be your opportunity to strike.
SequenceDialogue.9801033_TextContext: We need to isolate observers using a black box to prevent collapse.
SequenceDialogue.9804016_TextContext: There's no conventional way forward. Our databases show that the only way to progress is through stringification.
SequenceDialogue.9801072_TextContext: The Scissors lured us here to defuse the bomb. They're stalling for time.
SequenceDialogue.9801008_TextContext: With new patients being diagnosed, another round of memory erasure and reconstruction has begun...
SequenceDialogue.9801036_TextContext: It can be assumed that a theoretical 100% purity is possible.
SequenceDialogue.9801067_TextContext: Unlike the Type P-4, the program logic of each group is different...
SequenceDialogue.9801005_TextContext: Hmm, it's about time. They should be here by now.
SequenceDialogue.9801030_TextContext: Therefore, the perfect string sequence mentioned in the theory of decayless reproduction used to be impossible.
SequenceDialogue.9801069_TextContext: They put a lot of effort into deciphering it...
SequenceDialogue.9800006_TextContext: In Strinova, there was no hunger, no cold, and no pain.
SequenceDialogue.9804009_TextContext: We've mapped out the terrain and plotted an ingress route. The program will provide a holographic projection in your eyes. Follow the path - you've only got one shot.
SequenceDialogue.9804032_TextContext: Coordinates 78,312. Vertical distance of 33. An excellent tactical position.
SequenceDialogue.9801007_TextContext: It took us a while to calm down the collapse syndrome patients...
SequenceDialogue.9801040_TextContext: No one has to lose precious memories...
SequenceDialogue.9801012_TextContext: Alright, as long as we can extract high-purity crystals, we'll find a way back to Earth!
SequenceDialogue.9801010_TextContext: If there's a day when I start showing the symptoms...
SequenceDialogue.9801039_TextContext: If collapse syndrome can be cured, Father will remember me! No one has to lose precious memories... Perhaps even The Scissors would be willing to accept this world?
SequenceDialogue.9801054_TextContext: A scholar's job is research. Since The Scissors want to go to war, Michele, this will be your combat training session!
SequenceDialogue.9801027_TextContext: Even if the purity reaches the expected level, it would only serve to delay the inevitable.
SequenceDialogue.9801041_TextContext: Perhaps even The Scissors would be willing to accept this world?
SequenceDialogue.9801025_TextContext: Will we be able to cure collapse syndrome?
SequenceDialogue.9801028_TextContext: As a Bablo Crystal transforms from a superposition to an eigenstate, the uncontrollable collapse may damage the string sequence.
SequenceDialogue.9801016_TextContext: Hopefully, crystals of this purity can help us open a spatial rift.
SequenceDialogue.9801024_TextContext: If the purification process is successful, Instructor Kokona... will we be able to cure collapse syndrome?
SequenceDialogue.9801063_TextContext: What should we do, Instructor Kokona?
SequenceDialogue.9801013_TextContext: We'll find a way back to Earth!
SequenceDialogue.9801014_TextContext: I've just received word from Meredith that P.U.S has improved the crystal purification method in Komos Tower; the process is about to be completed. Hopefully, crystals of this purity can help us open a spatial rift.
SequenceDialogue.9801046_TextContext: I have infiltrated the control center
SequenceDialogue.9801020_TextContext: I'll draw P.U.S' attention while you steal the crystals.
SequenceDialogue.9804013_TextContext: I can tell that you're getting the hang of this place.
SequenceDialogue.9804026_TextContext: Report. I've lost control over the AI guards!
SequenceDialogue.9804019_TextContext: Report. Ming has struck the Comos defense center. The system should be offline for around thirty minutes. Over and out.
SequenceDialogue.9804014_TextContext: Report. Kanami has made it to the Comos control room and should be disabling the alarm system within ten seconds. Over and out.
SequenceDialogue.9801006_TextContext: Sorry, we're late! It took us a while to calm down the collapse syndrome patients...
SequenceDialogue.9801065_TextContext: Defuse the bomb. I'll cover you.
SequenceDialogue.9804028_TextContext: Lawine, the guards are back online. The enemy's location is unknown. Let's start by determining the enemy's coordinates.
SequenceDialogue.9804005_TextContext: If everything has gone to plan, you should be inside the Comos defense system.
SequenceDialogue.9804034_TextContext: The amount of damage is somewhat lower than expected. Excellent! The Comos Center Console should be right in front of you.
SequenceDialogue.9804023_TextContext: Attack! This should be the last of them.
SequenceDialogue.9801056_TextContext: Copy! Focus on your research, Yvette. Instructor Kokona and I will deal with The Scissors!
SequenceDialogue.9804039_TextContext: The enemy has bypassed the defense system and reached the center console.
SequenceDialogue.9801031_TextContext: The perfect string sequence mentioned in the theory of decayless reproduction used to be impossible.
SequenceDialogue.9804007_TextContext: Our time is running out. I'll guide you through. Ming and Kanami will assist from the outside.
SequenceDialogue.9804035_TextContext: Ming has made successful contact with Kanami.
SequenceDialogue.9800001_TextContext: The moon had been forever buried in an endless night.
SequenceDialogue.9801062_TextContext: It's too quiet here. Have we missed anything...
SequenceDialogue.9804020_TextContext: Copy that. Over to you, Lawine.
SequenceDialogue.9801015_TextContext: P.U.S has improved the crystal purification method; the process is about to be completed.
SequenceDialogue.9801026_TextContext: It's not that simple. Given the current progress of collapse syndrome, even if the purity reaches the expected level, it would only serve to delay the inevitable.
SequenceDialogue.9800002_TextContext: The sea beat and swelled, expanding its tendrils across the world.
SequenceDialogue.9800008_TextContext: But to humanity, was eternal life more “dream” or “fantasy?”
SequenceDialogue.9804024_TextContext: The target has been annihilated. Not bad.
SequenceDialogue.9801023_TextContext: Looks like the purification process is almost complete.
SequenceDialogue.9801068_TextContext: A different program? They put a lot of effort into deciphering it but left the demolition location unguarded... This doesn't seem like something The Scissors would do.
SequenceDialogue.9801055_TextContext: Michele, this will be your combat training session!
SequenceDialogue.9801075_TextContext: Darn it! Continue working on the bomb. I'm going to support Yvette!
SequenceDialogue.9800004_TextContext: What they found instead was a new world - Strinova.
SequenceDialogue.9801017_TextContext: Same as before. I'll cover you.
SequenceDialogue.9801034_TextContext: Taking into consideration that the impact of quantum fluctuations in the string-net liquid purification chamber is less than 3 Planck constants, it can be assumed that a theoretical 100% purity is possible.
SequenceDialogue.9801070_TextContext: But left the demolition location unguarded... This doesn't seem like something The Scissors would do.
SequenceDialogue.9804017_TextContext: As for here... If my calculations are correct, you'll be able to use the air current to give your jump an extra push! Just remember to keep stringifying!
SequenceDialogue.9801052_TextContext: Fay is also worried. The purification is almost complete.
SequenceDialogue.9801038_TextContext: Fay believes that collapse syndrome is theoretically curable.
SequenceDialogue.9801080_TextContext: Fay, did you hear that? 4 o'clock...
SequenceDialogue.9801009_TextContext: Personally, I don't want to experience either collapse syndrome or reincarnation... If the day comes when I start showing the symptoms... please put me out of my misery!
SequenceDialogue.9804031_TextContext: Calculations show that you'll have an injury chance of over 60% in a head-on confrontation. Modify the assault plan and find a new route.
SequenceDialogue.9804002_TextContext: It's good that we were prepared.
SequenceDialogue.9804012_TextContext: It's too far to cover on foot alone. Time to stringify and glide over there.
SequenceDialogue.9804001_TextContext: Is this the Comos internal defense system? Feels... dangerous.
SequenceDialogue.9801003_TextContext: Even cities are beginning to undergo reverstringification. The Collapse is imminent.
SequenceDialogue.9804010_TextContext: The path ahead is blocked. There's no choice - I'll have to wall-stick my way through.
SequenceDialogue.9801045_TextContext: Stay true to yourself until collapse syndrome is cured.
SequenceDialogue.9801043_TextContext: This expedition will not be a short one.
SequenceDialogue.9804037_TextContext: Enemy incursion detected at A3. Requesting support!

SequenceDialogueApartment.9611104_TextContext: “That's why we have to protect this world.”
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601004_TextContext: “It's because we are not yet lost.”
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604054_TextContext: She often says that classical art is safer.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501033_TextContext: ...I didn't expect it to be this simple. This kind of communication skill isn't in my negotiation manual.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146116_TextContext: All this time, I've held the same dream. I want to see everyone in this world have a place they can call home, no matter their age or status. You'll make it happen with me, won't you?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605034_TextContext: You keep yawning. Are you not sleeping well, Celestia?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605019_TextContext: Three days?! How could this... In my mind, it's only been a single day!!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605039_TextContext: Stop trying to be strong. Sit down!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605014_TextContext: It's not! We haven't seen each other at all in the last few days!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604012_TextContext: I'm okay. I just nearly burned out my brain fantasizing...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601018_TextContext: Stop right there! You need to take care of yourself!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603021_TextContext: Just don't hold on too tightly. You might burn yourself!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101025_TextContext: I must gather courage and determinations to be ready for adversities!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101006_TextContext: This is a little surprise for taking care of me all this time. I hope it can commemorate our time together!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105028_TextContext: Why do I seek your understanding when I'm tired? Perhaps I've come to rely on you. If just a little more.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604052_TextContext: I've been following it online for a long time, but I just couldn't pull the trigger. It's totally different in person, where you can really appreciate the impact of modern art!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604007_TextContext: I was the best volleyball player on my team for three years running!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603003_TextContext: I said I wanted to gaze at the stars together, but now that you're finally here, there aren't any in sight.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601009_TextContext: There was an explosion. You just happened to be nearby...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146118_TextContext: I don't know why, but every time we're together, my heart beats in a way that it hasn't before...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603007_TextContext: In other words... the forecast isn't always accurate.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146111_TextContext: I folded many stars today. If only my wishes could bring some form of blessing to others, how great that would be.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105205_TextContext: That's it for today's music sharing. We'll listen to your playlist next time.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603014_TextContext: From a spiritual point of view!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601021_TextContext: The feeling of those machines moving around my body is so weird...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603012_TextContext: Someone's got a high opinion of themselves!!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146068_TextContext: I seem to have heard your precious laughter. Turns out that the light I've been chasing all this time... was you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601011_TextContext: Just to be safe, I took you back to my clinic to get some rest.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603013_TextContext: ...I'm not sure why, but your words feel like starlight piercing through the clouds, shining itself on me.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602011_TextContext: But I'm not as confident it will suit anyone else's taste.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101011_TextContext: But that's the person I am. I aspire to be a gamer-style investigator!
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820028_TextContext: I've got a gift for you. As a show of thanks.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501018_TextContext: Y-You could be a friend of the Groves...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146205_TextContext:
You're also interested in rescue missions?
I know you mean well, but I'm sorry... I have to do these things myself.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101205_TextContext: It's impossible to resist teasing it, right? Here, you try!
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501023_TextContext: You didn't sound like a friend...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146055_TextContext: You've got mail. Could it be something important? Best not wait! Let's open it up and take a look!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105002_TextContext:
Are you really... that strong?
(Cough) What I meant was that I wanted to recognize your abilities.
Is my praise not worthy of your happiness?
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146067_TextContext:
You must be tired. Come here and rest for a while. I can help you work out the next battle plan...
Zzz...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105022_TextContext:
Hard to believe the Grove family experienced such internal strife, isn't it?
But as one who has lived through it, I'm acutely aware of the twists and turns of our family history.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105023_TextContext:
Want to partner up?
You'll find that I have exacting standards for those who work with me.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501012_TextContext: You want me as your business partner?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602001_TextContext: You're here! Just give me a moment. Things are a bit messy...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146203_TextContext: Oh, you're here?! Give me a moment. I just need to check what sort of rescue quests we have available right now.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501016_TextContext: I find your attitude... somewhat unexpected. The Grove family is reputable and respected in both the business and finance sectors. I don't see a single reason why you would say no.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105103_TextContext:
Would you like a cup of black tea? I brewed it myself.
Of course, if you'd rather not drink, that's fine with me. Hmph!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603035_TextContext: Look like we got a little more luck.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602009_TextContext: Why don't you give it a try? This is my first attempt at making jam.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604041_TextContext: To be honest, I don't know that much about Meredith, so I was hoping you could give me some ideas.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602034_TextContext: Actually, I made a few other flavors too...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601030_TextContext: There seems to be something broken in your heart...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601024_TextContext: Just hold on a little longer. I'll be done in no time.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101002_TextContext: Let me introduce myself again. My name is Michele. My hobbies are cats and video games...
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501030_TextContext: I would like to reiterate that the friendship I desire is one that's long-lasting and stable. You will be my most valuable ally. Your wishes and demands will also be respected to the greatest extent possible as reflected in the contract.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603023_TextContext: I'm not gonna be able to keep a straight face if we keep this up.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146058_TextContext: At that moment, I had a new goal. I want to be someone you can rely on. If you can assist me in this, I dare say we'll be able to help each other in times to come.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146207_TextContext: Even in a place like this, Strinova, often described as an idyllic homeland for humanity, there are so many who suffer in poverty. It's my duty to do something for them, no matter how small that “something” may be.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101010_TextContext: I never would've guessed you knew me so well. Truth be told, I never expected to receive such an extraordinary gift. I must thank you...
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101020_TextContext: I was slightly worried that you might not be into video games...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604022_TextContext: Just saying “thank you” lacks sincerity, so I want to get a gift for everyone!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101020_TextContext: Only when all battles have ended will I finally be able to game to my heart's content, right?
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101204_TextContext: As long as I'm home, my cat seems extra energetic!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146054_TextContext: It'll take all of us working together to put fear into the enemy's heart! We can do this!
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501017_TextContext: Darn it. I have never failed a business negotiation... Are you sure you don't want to reconsider? I'm hoping that...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605036_TextContext: Regret, guilt, self-blame... I lose track of time and end up only getting a little sleep.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605024_TextContext: Wha! How could this happen?! Such laziness... such carelessness and irresponsibility!
SequenceDialogueApartment.9603001_TextContext: Phew... So, this is what a consciousness link feels like.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101104_TextContext: Wow, that was a really cool anime episode!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605013_TextContext: Hehe. That's probably it. We just saw each other yesterday!
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101006_TextContext: You don't know, do you? That must be what it means to hide one's light under a bushel.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603020_TextContext: Take as much as you want. There's plenty more where it came from!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105024_TextContext: Hmpf! This is just typical for you, isn't it? Being rude like that!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101013_TextContext:
Eh? Did you write something on my hand?
Is this some kind of text-based game?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604006_TextContext: Waah. It's a pity that I'm busy with the Astral Sanctuary. I would have liked to give it a try...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605046_TextContext: Mmm... It's a bit noisy... but... peaceful...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605038_TextContext: Ehm... I just stood up too quickly. The blood rushed to my head...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605008_TextContext: Ehm. Forget it... You've already seen me like this anyway...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605029_TextContext: Ah, well... The important thing is to get in contact with everyone and head to the Astral Sanctuary. A lot of work must have piled up in my absence!
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501019_TextContext: Business cooperation is not in my area of expertise.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820006_TextContext: Ah! I forgot to introduce myself.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601008_TextContext: Ah... Maybe I said too much...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601015_TextContext: Ah. You haven't really given it much thought until now, am I right?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605035_TextContext: Um... When I'm alone, my mind tends to wander to all kinds of complicated feelings...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101005_TextContext: Hmm... another new piece of mail. Let's see what's inside!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604044_TextContext: Ah. So that's the kind of stuff that Meredith likes. I've got it!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601026_TextContext: That's more like it. Good job. I'm done now.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603036_TextContext: Mhmm! Today turned out to be an unexpected success.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9602003_TextContext: Mhm. I'm sure you'll ace the inspection.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146112_TextContext:
Hm? Is something the matter?
Don't be shy about asking me for help if you want it.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101004_TextContext: Heh, you would never guess it in a hundred years, but that person is actually...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605020_TextContext: I wanted to think more about the Astral Sanctuary and my mother, so I tried to create a quiet environment for myself...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602024_TextContext: It's just that I put a lot into making this jam. That's why I'm eager for some feedback.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601014_TextContext: That's why most people sign up for a check-up after they've been in Strinova for a while.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820014_TextContext: In my view, Navigators deserve a lot of respect.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601018_TextContext: To me, you've always been more like my senior - a peer.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601002_TextContext: I've chosen my future in this lost expanse.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501011_TextContext: Based on our previous cooperation, I am interested in establishing a long-term partnership with you. Together, we will be unstoppable!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604021_TextContext: Thanks to everyone's help, the Astral Sanctuary isn't in danger anymore.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105009_TextContext:
It's all thanks to you.
Don't give me that look. I know when to thank you, and I'll say it clearly!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603039_TextContext: It's probably because of a “certain someone!”
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501007_TextContext: With the election fast approaching, the Grove family shall become the leader of the business world for the next decade.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603034_TextContext: The forecast was a total mess!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604057_TextContext: That's great! Next time... let's go to an art exhibition together!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602033_TextContext: That's great! What a load off my mind...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602025_TextContext: But if I'm too anxious, I'll be putting pressure on you too.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820016_TextContext: To lose one's memory is to lose one's self. Only by relying on Navigators like you can people find themselves once more.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101022_TextContext: It's been a while since I played videos with other people at home. Do you think an adventure involving both an investigator and a navigator would be particularly interesting?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605027_TextContext: Okay! I've updated everyone on the situation.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605026_TextContext: Alright. I've sent a message to the group chat.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105021_TextContext:
I'd describe us as traveling companions now, but I'd much rather wish we were more!
Only feelings that have survived the crucible of adversity can stand the test of time.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820019_TextContext: If the day comes when I'm “reincarnated,” please make sure to transfer my memory back and help guide me... so that I can become Celestia once more.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501006_TextContext: If one were to compare the entire business world to a giant cruise ship, the leader would be the person steering the ship and determining its course.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146120_TextContext: If only these stars could be given to those who truly needed them, in the Astral Sanctuary. It does bring a modicum of hope to their lives. You'd be happy too, won't you?
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105020_TextContext:
My family's legacy teaches that we must look toward the future.
Only then, can we endure.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105012_TextContext:
By the way, there's something I forgot to tell you.
You have no right to look into my history without my express permission!
In any case, I know nothing about what will happen...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605032_TextContext: That's right! We've gotta recharge the communicator right away!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101011_TextContext:
I am very curious, particularly about anything to do with you!
Are you sure there's nothing you wanna tell me in confidence?
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101024_TextContext:
I can sympathize with Scissors feeling like their backs are up against the wall, but that doesn't justify their extreme methods...
Anyway, I can't understand it.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9604004_TextContext: Even someone like me... has a reason to fight.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601009_TextContext: I almost forgot about the task at hand!
SequenceDialogueApartment.9604007_TextContext: I hope that your gentleness can protect those around you, Navigator.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601017_TextContext: They help stabilize our mental state and allow us to find ourselves once more. To help protect against collapse syndrome.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604003_TextContext: Strian's always like this. It is a famous resort, after all!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604013_TextContext: Fantasizing...? It's times like these where I don't have a clue what's going through your mind.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601019_TextContext: The Navigator is a great doctor whom everyone respects.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501010_TextContext: Become a friend of the Grove family, Navigator!
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101012_TextContext: In our rare free time, Navigator, are you interested in a challenge between gamers?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601013_TextContext: Though adverse reactions to stringification are rare, they're still a concern.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605011_TextContext: I wanted to see you, obviously!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604004_TextContext: Of course, the main reason is the beach volleyball competition held by the bay. It's been going on all week.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602006_TextContext: Of course, there's some for you too. That's why I invited you over!
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820029_TextContext: From now on, my memory is in your hands.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604055_TextContext: I'm happy you're willing to appreciate this kind of stuff with me...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604032_TextContext: As for Kokona... Oh? I didn't expect to find this here!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105005_TextContext:
Don't forget to check your mail.
If it were anyone other than you, I would not take such great pains to remind you of this!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105003_TextContext:
Ehm... I'm not good at comforting others... Hey you, how do you want to console yourself?
Would you prefer a pat on the shoulder or your head?
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105206_TextContext:
What? Do you not understand what I'm saying?
Come and sing with me!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604014_TextContext: Then again, I also get the feeling that it's a blessing I don't know what you're thinking right now...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605012_TextContext: I feel as if we haven't seen each other in a while... am I just overthinking things?
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820008_TextContext: As I'm sure you know, Urbino provides funding to members who run public welfare organizations.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601012_TextContext: You're still a newcomer to Strinova, right?
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601021_TextContext: You'll need to use a memory chip to link with me and record all my actions.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146406_TextContext:
Want to fold some stars up with me?
But before that, we might want to figure out what kind of wish we'd like to make.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105203_TextContext:
Wha?! I wasn't secretly listening to rock!
I can't believe you would suddenly show up out-of-the-blue without saying something first...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605047_TextContext: I'll... take a break... for a while...
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601003_TextContext: I've never forgotten what you said.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146108_TextContext: I won't hide anything from you, but... why are you touching that place? I'm not quite sure how to describe my feelings on the topic, and even less on what they mean...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101012_TextContext: I'm not a little kid anymore! Hehehe!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101026_TextContext: I've never regarded naivety as a personal fault. Perhaps behind those willful dreams, there really is a world in which everyone would like to live.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146059_TextContext: It's been a while, hasn't it? Each day apart feels like three autumns of longing. An eternity of separation... Please, could you not stay away for so long next time? I've really grown used to you staying by my side.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601014_TextContext: We arranged a Mindlock Inspection today to check and record my conditions.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820022_TextContext: I'll perform my duties as a Navigator.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105106_TextContext: I didn't come here on purpose. I'm just curious about what you've been working on.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605005_TextContext: I'm home... You're being too loud. The neighbors are going to complain...
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820010_TextContext: I was one of the first on the scene after receiving the rescue mission from Area 88 and found you lying on the pavement.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105027_TextContext:
I don't deny the possibility of betrayal still exists, but if it were to be you, perhaps I could accept that...
Hmpf! You don't seem like you'd dare betray my trust anyway!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105011_TextContext: The only reason I'm still here is to keep a better eye on that which concerns me. It wasn't all for you!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604053_TextContext: I'm a huge fan of modern art, but mother likes the classics much more.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101028_TextContext:
I always felt like I had some kind of special calling in life... Like curing Collapse Syndrome, fighting off The Scissors, and stuff...
I'm not joking! I'm being serious!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604039_TextContext: I'm sure that Kokona will be able to feel your thanks...
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501013_TextContext: The relationship I would like to establish is more than just business...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105001_TextContext:
This type of victory doesn't satisfy you, am I right?
Why don't we go for another?
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501020_TextContext: That's... That's not what I meant! I said, “friend.”
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601007_TextContext: My home in Star Street is only a few blocks away from the bay. If you're game, I'd be happy to take you to enjoy the sights.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605016_TextContext: I've just been home a day, haven't I?
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501004_TextContext: I'm going to tell you something you're probably already aware of.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603005_TextContext: I read the forecast carefully. There should have been stars out tonight.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820007_TextContext: I'm Celestia. I work as a medic of Urbino. This is my dorm in the Astral Sanctuary.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501002_TextContext: Audrey Grove, current head of the Grove Corporation. A pleasure to meet you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501014_TextContext: I'm a navigator, not a businessperson...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105026_TextContext:
When I lost my memory, everything around me felt alien.
But this experience taught me that what matters most isn't glory, fame, or fortune but rather the true purity of feeling.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820011_TextContext: I took a look at your ID, and it turned out you were my Navigator. Such serendipity.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101001_TextContext: As I thought, I do believe you have won!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603015_TextContext: My light and warmth - I've got plenty to spare for Celestia!
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501028_TextContext: I was quite sincere with you!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101023_TextContext: I believe Strinova must uphold law and order for its citizens to enjoy peaceful, happy lives.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101022_TextContext:
What justice means to me?
This isn't a question one can answer easily.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146109_TextContext: I love this world. There are so many things that make me feel anxious and ill at ease. It could be that nothing I do will change anything... But we must press on. Always.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105004_TextContext: I understand you must be very unhappy about it... That's why, in the next battle, you're gonna have to get them back with me!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146115_TextContext: I've been waiting for you. Thanks for coming.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602010_TextContext: It tasted pretty good to me.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602031_TextContext: I think it's definitely a taste that everyone should try!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146117_TextContext: Nothing I've done until this point has received the least amount of recognition from my mother... Perhaps she feels that I should have walked the same path as her. Do you think I was wrong?
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820023_TextContext: I still don't really get what it means to be a Navigator...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101103_TextContext: The latest episode of the show I've been watching is about to air. I have to finish my meal quickly and go watch it!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602005_TextContext: I figured I'd make some jam to give away.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501009_TextContext: What does all this have to do with me?
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820018_TextContext: That's why I took the liberty of tracking you down. I need you to help capture my memories.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604051_TextContext: Thanks to you, I've picked out some great gifts!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105006_TextContext:
Take it. It's a gift.
Doing nothing would hardly be an act of gratitude...
In any case, I just felt like giving you a little praise.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105105_TextContext: They say similarity in your taste in tea indicates similarity in many other areas as well.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9604006_TextContext: From now on, you may encounter more people and challenges.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820025_TextContext: Alright. I'm off to the Departure Zone. There's a P.U.S rescue mission that I'm needed for.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820030_TextContext: Now, then, you're free to explore Strinova.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9602005_TextContext: Approaching Anchor Point: Area 88 P.U.S Rescue Mission.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146107_TextContext:
Don't worry, I don't usually travel armed.
But something tells you're worried about something...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605017_TextContext: It's been three days since you've left your dorm!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603004_TextContext: Aren't the stars of Strian artificial?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601006_TextContext: Strian seems pleasant. Green trees, the seaside, and idyllic farms. It's a great place to relax.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603006_TextContext: Strian was built to simulate a real world. That's why it follows the natural laws of Earth.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604048_TextContext: It ticks the “dog” and “pyramid” boxes, and the design is pretty avant-garde!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105010_TextContext: Since you've expressed your admiration with such sincerity, allow me to accept your present. After all, that is not impermissible... Hmph. Stop overthinking it!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603024_TextContext: Tonight's atmosphere should be a solemn one. But, you being here with me...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105025_TextContext: Do you understand? I'm not one for changing my mind easily.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820009_TextContext: That's what the Astral Sanctuary does. We provide treatment to Strinovians in need.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604023_TextContext: Aren't you lacking money right now?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602003_TextContext: I helped treat some of the workers at the reserve. I guess this was their way of paying me back.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604035_TextContext: It's a model from an old Urbino multi-dimensional art collection!!!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604038_TextContext: This one's definitely gonna leave her speechless. Not a bad choice!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603032_TextContext: It's a shooting star! It's gotta be!
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820013_TextContext: That's right. It was your first day... you must not be used to the title yet.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601016_TextContext: That's right. Carrying out scheduled inspection is part of your job as a Navigator.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605018_TextContext: You're misremembering things. Two days have already passed!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602023_TextContext: Oooh... My bad. I shouldn't be rushing you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603019_TextContext: It's a warm light. I can feel it in my hands... That warmth...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146401_TextContext:
Good evening. Have you ever had the pleasure of eating ice cream late at night? It's a very special experience.
I've got a cup left. Why don't we share it?
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101106_TextContext: An anime expo is coming to Arton City soon! If you're free, would you come with me? There's a lot of merch I want to snap up!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603026_TextContext: If there are misfortunes, then surely there will be fortunes as well!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101021_TextContext:
Problems? Find an investigator!
I'm ready to depart on mission at any time!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603010_TextContext: With a shining star like me, do you really need any others?
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101013_TextContext: We have Paper Detective, a candidate for Best Story of the Year, and Superheroes of Justice, a classic action game that continues childhood memories. Which one would you like to play?
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501021_TextContext: Is this concept so difficult to understand... I would like you to be my navigator; for us to establish...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101014_TextContext:
Let's make a promise!
No matter what becomes of this world, we'll be together forever.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105204_TextContext: It doesn't hurt to listen to other genres once a in while.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105014_TextContext:
The Grove family doesn't need a haughty mistress. It needs a wise and proper leader.
I still don't know whether the person I am today is a proper reflection of all the hopes invested in me.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604026_TextContext: Meredith and Kokona... I wonder what would suit them?
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101203_TextContext:
Welcome home! That feels a bit weird... how about... Welcome back!
Hehe... that was pretty cute, wasn't it?!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605042_TextContext: Uhm... I... I seem to have subconsciously sat down...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604010_TextContext: Hm? You've got a strange expression on your face. Is the heat getting to you?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602019_TextContext: Hey, how do you find the taste?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601029_TextContext: Oi. What's with that despondent look?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605015_TextContext: Eh? Did I remember wrong? Didn't... didn't we just hang out yesterday...?
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146404_TextContext: Eh? You brought a dessert for me?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604018_TextContext: Eh?! My instincts tell me that I shouldn't follow this line of questioning any further...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101027_TextContext:
Justice is a belief. The ideal investigator should have the mettle to save the world!
But... just how much longer will it take me to become that kind of person?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601004_TextContext: I guess this counts as an excuse to stretch one's legs.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101016_TextContext: They also gave out cartridges for the game. Let's experience what it feels like to be the great detective!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101009_TextContext: Getting one of your presents always makes me happy!
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501005_TextContext: Urbino leader elections take place once a decade. This is a significant event in Urbino.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604056_TextContext: I'm a super open-minded person, after all!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605043_TextContext: The sofa and pillows... so soft... such a familiar scent...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604016_TextContext: It's fine. I don't want to be thought of as a weirdo, either!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605037_TextContext: Don't worry. I feel fine. I can get to work...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604025_TextContext: But that's fine! I'll get through it! These gifts are more important right now!
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820002_TextContext: An explosion on my first day...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604009_TextContext: I didn't think that Celestia would be so into sports!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601016_TextContext: I haven't. We adults are quite busy!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604049_TextContext: It's fine. Meredith's not the kind to complain anyway...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603037_TextContext: Shooting stars are heralds of good luck. It's a positive sign for the future.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605048_TextContext: And then... and then... back to work... work...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605021_TextContext: After that, I got lost in my thoughts and completely lost track of the outside world...
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101010_TextContext: An investigator slash gamer. Does it seem slightly out of place?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603009_TextContext: Look! Aren't there two stars right here?
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501031_TextContext: Now, would you consider... being my friend?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601031_TextContext: I'm no longer the person I once was...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604028_TextContext: Bai Mo already told me he wants me to convert all my thanks into money.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604024_TextContext: Yeah. I'm afraid that for the near future, I'll just have to keep myself going in the cheapest ways I can...
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601010_TextContext: When I saw you out cold, I checked your body for injuries, but I didn't find any.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146119_TextContext: See that light? It's from the indoor planetarium. At least it lets me see the stars even when the weather is patchy.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603025_TextContext: It's incredible. It feels like you've completely turned everything on its head...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604050_TextContext: Such a weird style. I feel like I've seen another side to Celestia today...
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820003_TextContext: It must be rough for you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602029_TextContext: Such expertise! I've only seen gourmets taste like this before.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601017_TextContext: I didn't even know about it. But when I'm on the battlefield...
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820027_TextContext: This is the first time our consciousnesses have connected... Thank you very much for your cooperation!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605022_TextContext: Wait a moment. I know I had the communicator on. The communicator... where's it gone?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601011_TextContext: It's nothing important. No need to worry!
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101019_TextContext: It's time to find out how well we work together as a team. Show me what you've got, Navigator!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604029_TextContext: And... he even gave me the exchange rate. I mean, the exchange rate between my sincerity and cash...
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501008_TextContext: And I happen to be the most promising candidate in the upcoming election!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602035_TextContext: Maybe you can help me taste those, too?
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501034_TextContext: You're truly a worthy ally of mine, having easily accomplished such a feat. I must not underestimate you.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820015_TextContext: Ever since the outbreak of collapse syndrome, the people of Strinova go through a memory reset once every hundred years.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105104_TextContext: Petals and candied fruit combined with the richness of the black tea. Truly a perfect blend.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602004_TextContext: I appreciate the gift. It's just... I've been scratching my head thinking about what to do with all these apples.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603033_TextContext: I only saw the tail end, but it couldn't be anything else!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604015_TextContext: That might have been a little rude...
SequenceDialogueApartment.15105013_TextContext:
If you think this brings us closer together, you're very badly mistaken!
But... If you show enough sincerity, perhaps I can give you some consideration...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604030_TextContext: Ick! Such poor form. What a shameless guy...
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820021_TextContext: Everything you record will be stored inside, so keep it safe.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101003_TextContext: Speaking of games, if you regularly visit The No.1 Gaming Forum, you must have heard of the famous moderator, Super Pawtector. She frequently updates game guides and shares gaming news...
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820024_TextContext: Oh right! Given that it's your first day, you've probably never done this before.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101105_TextContext: Mmm? Have you come to play again? I was just about to put on the next episode... But I suppose I can accompany you for a moment.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101002_TextContext: Eh? Who do I find the most powerful? You, of course!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602026_TextContext: Don't mind me! Take your time!
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820020_TextContext: Please use your memory chip to record those memories tied to me.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601023_TextContext: Please relax. Being anxious isn't going to help the examination go by any faster. Stop being such a child.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820026_TextContext: This will be a good opportunity to record the mission and get familiar with your work.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501001_TextContext: Excuse me, are you the Navigator? We worked together during the Grove Bank Incident. Do you remember?
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501024_TextContext: Isn't that how cooperation is supposed to be?!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146056_TextContext: Thank you for always staying by my side. I've wanted to give you this gift for a long time. Please... you must take this.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146057_TextContext: Thank you for always staying by my side.
SequenceDialogueApartment.9604002_TextContext: Do you also need to work in the field?
SequenceDialogueApartment.9604001_TextContext: Thank you for your hard work.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15101004_TextContext: Come here, and listen to me! I don't care about winning or losing. As far as I'm concerned, you're already incredible!
SequenceDialogueApartment.9820017_TextContext: For reasons unknown, the “The Second Collapse” occurred much earlier than the previous one. I'm worried that my reverstringification has been accelerated, too.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604019_TextContext: Let's get back to the topic at hand - gifts!!
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601013_TextContext: Oh! I forgot to introduce myself. I'm Celestia. As you can see, I run the Astral Sanctuary.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146113_TextContext:
I remember that maneuver.
I wonder if I might expect a little something in return?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605040_TextContext: I've gotta be strict. Sit down!
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101018_TextContext: This series was already popular back on Old Earth. It is a co-op role-playing game.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101008_TextContext: How did you tell? You do have a keen eye.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146066_TextContext: I accept responsibility for the entire matter. You don't need to lose sleep over it.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604005_TextContext: It's a tradition around these parts. The winning team gets to eat for free at Strian's most exclusive restaurant for an entire year!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146052_TextContext: This was a real team effort.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604031_TextContext: Is he the incarnation of some strange creature? The kind that swallows gold...
SequenceDialogueApartment.9603003_TextContext: I picked up this gift for you yesterday. Please, accept my gratitude!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601028_TextContext: It's rare to find someone in such good shape. Don't slack off now!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146065_TextContext: This wouldn't have been possible without everyone's hard work. So I thank you for your help. I hope that I can continue to stay by your side.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146305_TextContext: From this distance, I can see your face clearly. Mind if we savor this moment a bit longer? Just drag it out, however slightly?
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146307_TextContext: From this distance, I can see your face clearly. Mind if we savor this moment a bit longer? Just drag it out, however slightly?
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101015_TextContext: This is a new text adventure game with a thrilling plot and plenty of suspense based on the TV series of the same name. Even the senior officers at the Sentinel Bureau are recommending it.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10501029_TextContext: Here is a contract. I hope you don't mind. It's a family tradition; we have always valued contracts and commitments.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604037_TextContext: Kokona's gift has been decided! What do you think?!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605009_TextContext: So... Why did you come here...?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604040_TextContext: Kokona's decided, then. Next up, we need to find something for Meredith.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101009_TextContext: Let's get to know each other a bit better, shall we? I work as an investigator, but when I'm not on the job, I am Michele, the gamer. My ID is Super Pawtector.
SequenceDialogueApartment.10101021_TextContext: From now on, you'll be my gaming buddy! Here is your controller. Give it a try. You can adjust the sensitivity and shortcut buttons if necessary.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602013_TextContext: I'll be the first to brave this frontier of flavor!
SequenceDialogueApartment.9601020_TextContext: So... how should we go about this?
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604036_TextContext: They only put out a limited release of a thousand models, and they all sold out within minutes of launch. To be able to find one of them at such a small store... today's my lucky day!
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146103_TextContext:
I'm at your service.
Just holler at me when I'm needed.
SequenceDialogueApartment.15146208_TextContext:
I'm at your service.
Just holler at me when I'm needed.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601033_TextContext: Since you're here in Strian, let me treat you to a local delicacy - bonsai cake!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605002_TextContext: (She hasn't left her dorm in several days!)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601034_TextContext: (Afterward, Celestia treated me to a delicious bonsai cake, but I still feel differently than I did before...)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602018_TextContext: (The hellishly sweet taste rushed down my throat and coated my every sense, sending shivers down my spine.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604034_TextContext: (Its tendrils, each covered with myriad eyes, twist into a ball-shaped object. Only the three wings on its back recall the imagery of angels...)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605023_TextContext: (Pointing) Under the table. It's out of energy.
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604002_TextContext: (Feeling boxed in) This really is a tourist trap. Look at how many people showed up!
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605001_TextContext: (Star Street, Strian, the door to Celestia's dorm... what am I doing here...?)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603001_TextContext: (Strian. The bay a few blocks down from the reserve. The cold wind blows against the rushing waves in a loud song.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603031_TextContext: (In the empty night sky, a bright star suddenly began streaking across the expanse before quickly disappearing under the sea.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604033_TextContext: (Celestia holds up a wood carving. The base of it reads “angel”... Eh? Is this thing really an angel?!)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14602015_TextContext: (As Celestia carefully produced the jam and twisted off the lid, a sweet aroma escaped from the jar. This sweet aroma...?)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604046_TextContext: (Celestia produces what seems to be a dog sewn from cloth. At least it looks like a dog. Probably.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14601020_TextContext: (Her face growing serious, Celestia pushed me down onto the chair and started attaching strange instruments to my body.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14603017_TextContext: (All of a sudden, Celestia stretched out her hands in my direction, with care, as if she were picking up something from the void.)
SequenceDialogueApartment.14605045_TextContext: (Whispering) Go to sleep... go to sleep... go to sleep...
SequenceDialogueApartment.14604047_TextContext: (Its big head made out of black cloth is completely disproportionate to its small body. There's a pyramid on its head for some reason. One of its eyes is way smaller than the other. Its tooth seems to be made out of some kind of bone polished to look like a real dog's tooth. Why was so much effort put toward realism in this one area...?)

SequenceMap.97003_Desc: Area 88 was one of the first areas established in Neutroville. It's home to some of the world's oldest buildings and still serves as a busy traffic artery and commercial hub today.
SequenceMap.97002_Desc: Bablo Crystals consist of two components: the crystal body itself and the virtual matter inside. The virtual matter is of no use to Strinovians, meaning that crystals need to be purified before use.
SequenceMap.97013_Desc: The Komos Tower defense system exists in a virtual space that imitates the environment of the [True Wilderness]. Intruders are subject to an overwhelming sense of discomfort and disorder, before eventually succumbing to the fate of reverstringification.
SequenceMap.97001_Desc: Komos Tower serves as the energy hub for each city. The String Energy generated by the resonance of abundant Bablo Crystals maintains regional stability, suppressing the occurrences of [Collapse Syndrome] and [Reverstringification].

Choose how in-game sounds such as footsteps, gunfire, and ability effects are presented, with each option providing different 3D spatial effects.

System: Automatically changes based on your audio setup.

HRTF: 3D surround sound via headphones with sound distinguished between the front and rear. Make sure to disable other 3D sound programs when using HRTF.

7.1 Surround Sound: If supported, expands the sound field to distinguish sounds from all directions for more precise sound localization.

Dolby Atmos: If your device or environment supports it, experience immersive Dolby Atmos sound that envelopes from above and around you, placing you at the forefront of the game. Enjoy an intense and thrilling atmosphere as if you're transported into the game itself.
Setting.506_Tips:
Use spatial audio effects for in-game sounds.

If you encounter audio lag, you may be able to resolve the issue by lowering the spatial audio.
If you cannot hear gunshots or footsteps, there may be a hardware compatibility issue. Try disabling spatial audio or changing the audio output to HRTF.

Skill.1285_Intro: The Pulse Blade's scan slows enemies trying to escape its zone with an Electromagnetic Chain.
Skill.1286_Intro: The Pulse Blade remains active, rescanning when enemies enter its range, until the skill's duration ends.
Skill.1195_Intro: Cage radius shrinks every second after Eika casts an active skill until the minimum radius is reached.
Skill.1156_Intro: Flavia gains temporary armor equivalent to a percentage of the DMG dealt to the Phantom Orb before it is depleted or destroyed.
Skill.1153_Intro: Flavia generates a Phantom Zone at her location. Enemy fatal attacks within the zone trigger her brief butterfly transformation. This effect does not apply to enemies outside the zone, who can only spot Flavia if she attacks first.
Skill.1151_Intro: When attacked, Flavia briefly becomes invincible and summons a Phantom Orb at her location that obstructs enemy vision but can be destroyed.
Skill.1152_Intro: Flavia's active skill CD reduces when she takes DMG; Upon taking significant DMG, she gains temporary ultimate points, valid for the current round.
Skill.1104_Intro: The passive skill now triggers an intense visual obstruction effect on enemies.
Skill.1375_Intro: Enemies detected by the Sonar Disk are tracked. If they stay within range for a set duration, they will become disoriented, experiencing a reduced firing rate.
Skill.1085_Intro: Nobunaga and his team can see enemies entering his device's domain, and the effect continues briefly after they leave.
Skill.1051_Intro: Audrey enters Deployment Mode to greatly increase her firing rate with no recoil and without needing to reload. Extended firing causes weapon overheat, temporarily disabling shooting.
Skill.1076_Intro: A view-blocking bubble forms over the painted area, exploding upon contact and applying a paint debuff to enemies.
Skill.1374_Intro: Kanami's primary weapon now deals explosive AOE DMG.
Skill.1371_Intro: Kanami fires a Sonar Disk that scans for unobstructed enemies within a 180° arc in front of it. Detected enemies are revealed to her and her teammates.
Skill.1373_Intro: Kanami summons a holographic figure that attracts enemies within a certain range, reducing their movement speed and accuracy.
Skill.1372_Intro: Kanami's shots generate a Sonar Zone at the impact point. Enemies within this area are exposed.
Skill.1205_Intro: The character gains unlimited perfumes with stronger movement speed and rate of fire bonuses that do not attenuate, but which only apply to allies within range at the time of casting.
Skill.1215_Intro: The character gains unlimited perfumes with stronger movement speed and rate of fire bonuses that do not attenuate, but which only apply to allies within range at the time of casting.
Skill.1334_Intro: Allies gliding within the sandstorm are lifted upward by a powerful gust.
Skill.1336_Intro: The Sandstorm completely blocks the field of view.
